title: bill's cherry pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and undrained cherries.
Cook until mixture thickens and boils.
Pour into a 9-inch crust.
Top with "lattice" crust and sprinkle sugar on top. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Take out and spread butter on top of pie.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Add all vegetables (except broccoli) to chicken broth and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add broccoli to broth and simmer for five more minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir until melted.
Add flour to milk and stir until mixed together.
Now add to soup.
Stir frequently while broth is thickening.
Be careful not to let the milk scorch.

title: hidden valley potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; do not peel.
Slice crosswise.
Layer in casserole dish.
Pour melted oleo over potatoes; sprinkle with Hidden Valley mix.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour, salt and nutmeg; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.
Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: fudgy mocha frosting
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Add cocoa and water, stirring constantly until mixture thickens (do not boil).
Remove from heat.
Add liqueur.
Gradually add powdered sugar; beat with wire whisk until smooth.
Add water a little at a time until desired consistency.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add water and mix thoroughly.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water and add to mixture.
Cover.
This will make a sponge or starter for your bread.
According to your schedule, this may be left to develop for 2 to 12 hours.

title: grandma's sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, then peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes in fourths or sixths.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Place potatoes in butter for 3 to 4 minutes, then turn.
Sprinkle brown sugar over top of potatoes and continue to cook.
Turn and brown. Sprinkle brown sugar on opposite side and brown.
Serve hot.

title: cranberry relish or salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the boiling water.
Set aside.
Grind the first 5 ingredients together.
In bowl, mix sugar, pineapple and first 5 ground ingredients together.
Add jello to this, mix and chill until ready to serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking dish, then add peaches.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: standard pie pastry
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until it looks like small peas.
Then add water to hold together.
Use a cereal bowl to cut out rounds for fried apple pies.

title: honey apple crisp
directions: Spread sliced apples in a shallow baking dish; sprinkle with sugar and lemon juice and pour honey over all.
In a bowl, mix remaining ingredients and make a crumbly mixture.
Spread this over apples and bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm with cream.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix nuts and raisins in 1 cup flour; sit aside.
Cream sugar and butter, then add 1 egg at a time; mix well.
Add salt and flavoring.
Mix well; add remainder of 2 cups flour.
Add nuts and raisins; mix well.
Put in 10-inch tube pan and bake 2 hours in 325° oven.
Let cool to cut better.

title: mom's heavenly hash
directions: Break and melt chocolate bars in microwave at 1 minute intervals for 2 minutes. Stir each time. Add roasted pecan halves and marshmallows and quickly slip into 2 logs on foil sheets. Wrap with foil and refrigerate. Cut into 1/2-inch slices. (Keep in sealed container and cool place.)

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, milk, oatmeal, eggs, chopped onion, garlic powder, pepper, chili powder and salt.
Make golf ball size meatballs. Place in baking dish.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: orange cake
directions: Grind together raisins and orange peeling.
Cream together shortening or butter, sugar and eggs, then add raisin and orange peel and nuts.
In separate bowl, sift together flour and salt. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add alternately to the creamed mixture, the flour and milk mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes in a greased loaf pan or a Bundt pan.
Remove from oven and immediately add glaze.

title: zettie's chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add milk.
Cook until good and hot. Beat egg yolks and add to mixture.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add vanilla and a little butter.
Stir. Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: cranberry fruit bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 regular loaves.

title: violet's spinach casserole
directions: In first pan, cook spinach with onion according to package directions.
Do not salt the water; drain and squeeze dry.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender or food processor. Top with cover and process until mixture is smooth. Cover and chill dressing at least 1 hour.
Serve dressing with salad greens.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate fillers
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cream butter with brown sugar and salt.
Blend in flour and oats until particles are fine. Press about 2/3 of mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9 inch pan. Heat condensed milk in saucepan.
Stir in chips.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs; press down lightly.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes, or until light golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, nutmeg, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Alternate dry ingredients with 1 cup cooking oil, beating into pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° in loaf pans 40 to 45 minutes.
(Will make five 6 x 3-inch cakes or 2 larger loaves.)

title: 3 pepper beef tenderloin
directions: Trim fat from beef.
Mix remaining ingredients; rub over beef. Cover; refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°; covered 30 minutes, uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: multi-grain bread
directions: *Make oat flour by putting rolled oats in food processor.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding according to package.
Add Tang.
Prepare fruit in bite size pieces.
Mix with Tang pudding.
Chill.

title: lime jello pineapple fluff
directions: Make jello as directed on box.
Chill until almost jelled (check in about 50 minutes).
Put cream cheese in mixer and blend. Add crushed pineapple to cream cheese.
Add almost jelled jello into mixture of cream cheese and pineapple (beat until blended). Add Cool Whip and blend.
Place in 13 x 9-inch glass container and refrigerate (ready in about 2 hours).
Keep refrigerated until needed.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and roll in balls. Refrigerate until firm.
Melt in double boiler the remaining ingredients.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on wax paper to cool.

title: mother's sweet potato pie
directions: Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie - lorene
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Mix chicken, Veg-All, corn, soup mixes, onion and eggs.
Pour in large Pyrex ovenproof bowl.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar and milk in saucepan; boil 2 minutes.
Stir in coconut.

title: ham souffle
directions: Put 1/2 bread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Cover with slices of ham.
Cover with grated cheese.
Cover with other 1/2 of bread.
Combine milk, seasoned salt, nutmeg, salt, Worcestershire sauce and eggs.
Pour liquid mixture over bread; cover with foil. Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, cover with buttered crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter and hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In bowl, combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar and baking powder.
Add milk, oil and vanilla; stir until smooth. Stir in peanut butter.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper in a heavy skillet. Drain.
Line baking dish with 3/4 of the sausage mixture.
Combine eggs and sour cream.
Season to taste.
Pour over sausage mixture. Bake at 350° until eggs are semi-set.
Stir egg mixture and top with remaining sausage.
Bake until eggs are firm.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place shredded lettuce into straight edged bowl.
Spread each of the ingredients over the lettuce in order.
Do not stir. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with bacon bits or ripe olives before serving.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: turtle cake no. 264
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on package and pour half in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Melt caramels together with butter and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over baked cake and cover with remaining cake batter.
Sprinkle with 1 cup nuts and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: 20th century pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar gradually.
Add eggs one at a time. Add mace, then fold in flour.
Add flavoring.
Bake in a tube pan, greased and floured, at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Drain strawberries reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Beat cream cheese with the reserved liquid, thawed strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust. Refrigerate several hours.
Garnish with strawberry halves or kiwi fruit.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put on cookie sheet by spoonfuls. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until slightly brown. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put coarse salt over cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Soak in this solution for 3 hours, then drain.
Mix remaining ingredients, put this solution on stove; let come to a boil; stir; put cucumbers, peppers and onion in solution and let come to a second boil.
Put in clean, sterile jars; pour solution over pickles. Seal at once.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add shortening and banana; beat on low speed of mixer until combined.
Add buttermilk or sour milk, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Turn into greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add everything but cabbage.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Put cabbage in bottom of casserole dish and spoon on meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut oat cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine oats and baking soda; gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and peanuts. Drop by tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire racks to cool. Yield: About 8 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add nuts and maraschino cherries or coconut.
Shape into balls.
Freeze 3 to 4 hours.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup and 1/2 can onion rings. Put into a baking dish. Put the rest of onion rings on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend together pudding mix and milk with mixer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
In a large bowl, layer wafers, pudding and bananas until all is used.
Refrigerate.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix pasta, vegetables, olives and seasoning with 8 ounces of Italian dressing.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, add other 8 ounces of dressing.

title: apple, pecan and butterscotch pie
directions: Make crust for 2 crust pie.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients; fold in Cool Whip.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Cover with 1/2 of the pudding mixture, another layer of crackers and the remainder of pudding mixture.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.
Frost with frosting.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: dream salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: hot cider
directions: Stir starch and soda.
Mix in cold water and stir over heat until mixture has a consistency of mashed potatoes.
Turn onto a plate and cover with a damp cloth until cool enough to handle. Then knead.
Use immediately or store in airtight container.

title: banana pudding
directions: With an electric mixer, mix pudding and milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, make a layer of wafers, bananas and pudding.
Continue layers until finished.

title: easy no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, cocoa and oleo until it comes to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter.
Pour over the vanilla and oats.
Stir and drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: b~b~q brisket
directions: Lay brisket on heavy foil.
Sprinkle both sides with black pepper, onions, salt, garlic salt and celery salt.
Pour the bottle of liquid smoke over brisket.
Keep fat side on top to cook.
Seal tight and cook at 275 degrees for 5 hours.
Open foil and drain most (not all) liquid off.
Pour the bottle of BBQ sauce over brisket.
Reseal and cook one hour at 325 degrees.
Chill overnight, then slice.
Serves 6-8.

title: virginia fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken and soak overnight in salt water (about 2 ounces salt to 2 quarts water).
Drain well and dip chicken in buttermilk.
Mix together the flour, black pepper, Accent, celery seed, salt and garlic powder and put in bag.
Shake buttermilk dipped chicken pieces in and coat well with mixture.
Pan-fry in butter and oil in covered frying pan until tender, approximately 20 to 25 minutes, turning just once.

title: spaghetti sauce with lobster
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion and garlic in olive oil until tender (do not brown).
Remove garlic.
Add lobster and cook until red.
Remove lobster from pan.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add lobster and cook 1/2 hour longer.
Remove meat from lobster and add to sauce.
Simmer for 1/2 hour longer.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.

title: plain or coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Add 1 cup coconut (optional).
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in oven preheated to 300°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, eggs and cocoa; mix well, then add milk, water, baking soda, baking powder and flour.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In mixer bowl, cream sugar and shortening with electric mixer until light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk.
Add flour and bananas (beat until smooth after each addition).
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, take out and cool the
rest of the way.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet with butter flavor shortening.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Spray microwave-safe
10 x 6 x 2-inch dish with cooking spray. Combine mix, eggs and mayonnaise in a bowl.
Spread in prepared dish.
Microwave
at
half power (50%) for 6 minutes, turning once.
Turn again.
Microwave at full power (100%) for 2 or 3 minutes or until surface is firm to the touch.
Remove dish to wire rack to cool completely before cutting.
Makes 18 brownies.

title: banana split pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar well. Spread this over crust. Slice bananas over cream cheese mixture. Spread pineapple over bananas. Top with cool whip. Sprinkle top with cherries and pecans. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Stir over low heat until melted.
Add vanilla.
Put cereal in large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over all.
Mix thoroughly.
Then place powdered sugar and mixture in a large bag.
Close and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool. Store in airtight container.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix with mixer and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Lightly fry garlic and onion in oil mixed with paprika in a large Dutch oven.
Add pepper, oregano, green pepper and tomato sauce.

title: pimento-cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, add juice.
Mash pimentos in cream cheese with fork.
Add to jello.
Add pineapple, celery and walnuts.
Fold in topping.
Pour in mold.
Chill overnight.

title: goodbye turkey casserole
directions: Mix flour, half of salt and onion salt in bowl.
Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Stir flour mixture into butter, gradually stirring in milk.
Stir occasionally until thickened. Pour Minute rice into 2-quart shallow baking dish.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the sugars and milk, oil, egg and vanilla.
Sift into mixture the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Mix well.
Add nuts, oatmeal and zucchini.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onions, cheeses and bacon.
Set aside.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: bacon breakfast casserole
directions: Place 4 of the bread slices on bottom of greased 8-inch square baking dish; top with bacon, mushrooms, onions and cheese. Cover with remaining 4 bread slices.
Beat eggs and milk with wire whisk until well blended; pour over bread.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until center is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Stir in ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Shred or chop cabbage.
Place in bottom of 1-quart casserole dish or square cake pan.
Spoon hamburger mixture over top.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie(w.w.)
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter. Fold in milk and Cool Whip.
Pour over crust and freeze.
Yields 16 pieces, 2 points each; no crust - 1 point.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes; cut the potatoes in half.
Spoon potato out of skin, leaving about 1/4 inch of the potato in the skin.
Mix crumbled bacon, onion and cheese.
Fill potato skins with bacon mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 15 minutes, or until cheese has melted.

title: hush puppies (small)
directions: Mix in order.
Drop by spoon into preheated oil; cook until golden brown, about 3 minutes.

title: deep fried chicken
directions: Combine flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken pieces in flour, into milk and then flour again.
Fry for 20 minutes or until golden brown or done.
Do not crowd chicken pieces while frying.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and milk in a saucepan; place over heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Boil, without stirring, 4 minutes until mixture forms a soft ball when drizzled in cold water. Remove from heat. Beat by hand until mixture is cool and thickened. Beat in vanilla.

title: glazed fruit pie
directions: 1st Layer:
Cream 1/2 cup margarine with 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup oil.
Add 1 egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add salt, soda, cream of tartar and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Mix.
Put in pizza pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken, seasoned with salt, pepper, lemon pepper, chopped onions, chicken bouillon and red pepper.
When done, drain and reserve broth.
Cool and chop into bite size pieces.
Heat broth to a rolling boil and add spaghetti.
Let it come to a boil again and stir just to separate.
Turn off heat.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add softened cream cheese.
Add eggs, vanilla and almond.
Continue to beat for 5 minutes.
Mix in flour and baking powder, a little at a time. Grease tube pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Test with toothpick.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over cake.

title: country style vanilla ice cream
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until thickened.
Add cream, vanilla and salt; mix thoroughly.
Pour into can.
Add milk to fill line on can and stir well.
Freeze as directed with ice cream freezer.
Makes approximately 4 quarts.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Gradually add flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: really good chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine with sugars until light.
Beat in vanilla and egg until smooth.
Mix together flour, soda and salt, but don't sift; beat into batter.
Add chocolate chips and nuts and stir to mix thoroughly.
Drop onto lined baking sheets using a small ice cream scoop and bake for 12 minutes turning sheets end for end and trading oven racks (top to bottom) at the halfway point.
Remove from oven and leave until cookies are barely cool enough to handle, then transfer to racks to cool.
Makes 60 large cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on box. Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Add chicken and soup to macaroni and cheese.
Mix in 1/2 of onion rings, reserving the rest for topping.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375° or until bubbling. Sprinkle remainder of onion rings on top and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini toss
directions: Saute fresh zucchini in hot oil for 5 minutes or until crisp-tender. Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes. Spoon into serving dish.

title: chocolate mint dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk and spread onto mint layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal hermits
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonsful onto foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute before removing to racks to cool.
Great for anytime, but especially good for mailing to hungry college students.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Wash beans in warm water.
Combine beans, water, onion, salt and pepper in a large pot.
Cook on medium heat for 2 hours.
Add ham hocks and bacon.
Cook 2 more hours.

title: shortcakes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients until soft dough forms.
Gently smooth dough into ball on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 3-inch cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 shortcakes.

title: hot drink mix
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in an airtight container in a cool dry place for up to 6 months.
Yield: 15 batches.

title: hamburger cheese nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
When cheese is melted, it is ready to serve.

title: harvest lasagna(meatless)
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons each of butter and oil in a large frying pan.
Add onion and garlic; cook until soft.
Toss in eggplant and brown 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, peppers, tomatoes, salt, basil and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes, then remove lid and cook over medium heat about 10 minutes.
Set aside.

title: basic sweet batter for fritters
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt. In bowl, beat remaining ingredients with mixer until well mixed.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until smooth.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring over medium heat to 236° on candy thermometer or until a little mixture dropped in cold water forms soft ball.
Remove from heat and let stand for 15 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add flavoring; beat until mixture starts to lose its gloss (about 8 minutes).
Stir in the candied cherries and walnuts.
Quickly pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds fudge.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add water slowly, stirring until smooth and thick.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks, butter, lemon juice and rind.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour into the baked pie crust.

title: martha's barbecue chicken
directions: In large baking dish or crock-pot, combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° until done.

title: spiced or russian tea
directions: Boil water with sugar and allspice in it.
Add tea that has been steeped.
Add juices; simmer for several hours.
Will keep in the refrigerator several weeks.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until cooked.
Remove chicken from bones.
Cut into small pieces.
Add green onions and celery.
In separate container, mix sour cream, mayonnaise and Lawry's salt.
When thoroughly mixed, add to chicken.
Refrigerate until served.

title: vegg nog
directions: Blend all ingredients until very smooth.
Chill.
Experiment with the proportions to obtain the degree of thickness and flavor you desire.

title: apple cake
directions: Set aside 3/4 cup sugar and apples, mixed together.

title: witches' brew
directions: Place ingredients in large saucepan.
Cover; heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Chill 1 hour before serving with vegetables or chips.

title: savory chicken casserole
directions: Blend soup and broth.
Heat and stir until smooth and hot. Add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup of cheese.
Pour into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Brown sausage in large skillet.
Drain off excess fat, if necessary.
Add green pepper, onion and celery, saute until vegetables are slightly tender.
Cook grits in water with salt, according to directions.
Combine grits and sausage mixture. Put 1 cup cheese in mixture.
Pour into buttered shallow 2-quart casserole.
Spread undiluted soup over sausage mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage squares
directions: Mix hamburger and sausage, brown and drain off grease.
Add rest of ingredients, stir and spoon onto rye bread slices. Sprinkle with oregano and broil a few minutes, until cheese bubbles, just before serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour, Crisco and milk.
In saucepan, combine water and sugar.
Heat until sugar is melted.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Roll dough out into a rectangle.
Put chopped fruit onto rolled out dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon if you like.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut into 1-inch slices. Put slices into melted butter, single layer.
Pour sugar-water mixture over it.
Bake 1 hour or until golden brown at 350°.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and sugar and mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls and dip into melted chocolate. Place balls on wax paper and let sit until chocolate is hard.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook at 350° until browned.

title: fide's chile verde(authentic)
directions: Boil tomatoes and chiles for 10 minutes in 3 cups water.
In large skillet, brown meat in with lard.
Blend chiles, tomatoes, salt and garlic clove and 1/2 cup water together.
Pour over meat and bring to a boil.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Taste to make sure it has enough salt.

title: lentil and vegetable soup
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in skillet and saute onion and garlic until tender.
Set aside. In a large pot, add beef broth, oil, lentils, carrots, potatoes, onions, garlic, bay leaf, salt and pepper.

Bring to a boil and allow to simmer uncovered about 30 minutes or until lentils and vegetables are cooked thoroughly. If the broth starts to evaporate, add water until soup is the desired consistency.

title: yogurt salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Prepare about 6 hours before using for flavors to blend.
Delicious on green salads.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dressing.
Also good as a raw vegetable dip.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain green beans and corn.
Mix all ingredients well and put in casserole.
Cover top with crushed crackers and almonds.
Pour melted butter over crackers and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Blend all together.
Grease pan; butter top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be frozen.

title: fran's broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and place in square casserole.
Top with 1 cup sharp cheese, grated.
Mix together crackers and melted butter.
Place on top of casserole ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 24 hour macaroni salad
directions: Cook pasta and cool.

title: apple dumplings with pineapple sauce
directions: Sift flour with salt.
Cut in shortening until like coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir just enough to blend.
Turn out on floured surface and roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in 5-inch squares. Pare apples.
Cut in eighths.
Place about 6 pieces on each square.
Sprinkle generously with sugar, cinnamon
and nutmeg. Dot with butter.
Fold corners to center and pinch edges together securely with fork.
Arrange dumplings in large greased pan and pour over pineapple sauce.
Bake in a moderately hot oven (375° to 400°) until pastry is brown and apples tender.

title: best fresh strawberry pie
directions: Glaze:
Mash 1 pint of strawberries.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Stir into crushed strawberries.
Add water.
Stir over low heat and bring to gentle boil until thickened.
Add oleo and cool.

title: onion cheese chicken
directions: Microwave butter in small bowl on High for 1 to 1 1/4 minutes. Stir in salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour seasoned butter over chicken.
Cover with wax paper; microwave at High for 5 minutes.
Turn pieces over.
Top with mushrooms.
Cover with wax paper; microwave 4 to 5 minutes.
Top with French onion rings and cheese.
Microwave at High, uncovered, for 1 to 2 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: low-fat chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Mix egg and milk together.
Crush corn flakes. Dip washed chicken in milk and egg mixture.
Roll in corn flakes. Spray dish with Pam.
Place chicken in dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab mousse spread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix the soup, water and gelatin together; place on low heat to dissolve. Add to he cheese mixture and blend well.
Pour into greased mold. Let set overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: congo squares
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Pour batter into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 35 minutes.
Wait until cooled, then cut into squares.

title: buttermilk-buckwheat pancakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl; make a well in center of mixture.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan and crumble.
Add rice to drippings; stir until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring all the time.
Add bacon, onion and peas.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes, turning constantly.
Season with soy sauce and pepper. Yields 4 servings.

title: heath bar - chocolate covered toffee
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil. Arrange crackers to cover foil.

title: tomato sauce puttanesca
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until golden.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer and cook for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press hamburger into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle on onion.
Cover with vegetables, cheese, soup and last tater tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: trail bologna(makes 2 rolls)
directions: Mix and roll in 2 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Then bake in shallow pan at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: efi chicken
directions: Mix to make marinade.
Pour over chicken parts and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tofu-sweet potato pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender or food processor until thoroughly blended and free of lumps.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut bread into 1-inch thick slices and lay in pan.
Beat all other ingredients, pour over bread and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until puffy and light brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: chicken in red wine
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in skillet.
Cook chicken over moderately high heat about 6 to 7 minutes.
Turn and cook 5 minutes more.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Stir to blend.
Cook 1 minute.
Sprinkle with flour. Add wine and chicken broth, bring to boil.
Add bay leaf, thyme and more salt and pepper if needed.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Mix next 4 ingredients and add to yeast mixture.
Divide dough in half.
Roll in wax paper.
Put 1/2 of dough on bottom of large cookie sheet with sides.
Pour on cream cheese mixture.
Put remaining half of dough on top.
Let rise 1 hour.

title: stove top cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Cook 1 minute at a rolling boil, then add last 2 ingredients.
Spoon onto wax paper and let set until firm.

title: eggplant parmesana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut eggplant into thin slices.
In 1/4 cup oil, cook eggplant until lightly browned.
Add more oil, as needed.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce over bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange a layer of eggplant; sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in oil about 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, eggs, crumbs, milk, Parmesan cheese, onion, salt and oregano.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove any liquid in pan.
Spoon pizza sauce over loaf top. Cover with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Bake for 10 minutes. Saute green peppers, mushrooms and parsley.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil.
Extend foil over edges.
Combine sugar, evaporated milk and margarine in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat to boil.
Clip candy thermometer to side of pan.
Cook, stirring frequently over medium heat to 234°.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Remove thermometer.
Add Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter, walnuts and vanilla. Pour into pan.
Score fudge into squares while warm and garnish by pressing additional walnuts into fudge.
When firm, cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: rice cooker cabbage casserole
directions: Measure rice and water, using Hitachi cooker measuring cup. For low fat diet, I precook meat and sausage a little to remove excess fat.
Then put all ingredients in large bowl and mix well. Then pour in 8 to 10 cup Hitachi rice cooker.
Start cooker.
Let stand in cooker pot for 1 hour after bell rings before serving.

title: tea for cough
directions: Add thyme to hot water. Cool. Add honey. Take a teaspoon every hour. It really works!

title: greton
directions: Put ground pork in kettle with salt, pepper, onion and garlic. Cover with water; cook about 4 to 5 hours slowly or until all water has gone.
Remove from burner; add cloves and cinnamon.
Beat it a little and pour in dish; stir it a few times while cooling.
Good on both crackers or toast.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Coat all sides of meat with vinegar.
Then repeat with flour. In a Dutch oven, heat the oil until hot.
Brown the meat slowly on all sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add chopped onion (sauteed).
Add water or desired liquid, thyme, Worcestershire sauce, onion soup mix and cream of mushroom soup; stir.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Add desired vegetables; continue baking, covered, 45 minutes or until tender.

title: care-free casserole
directions: Combine peas, carrots, soup, water and milk in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Spoon half of it into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spoon rice over vegetables; mix. Layer chicken over rice.
Sprinkle with salt.
Top with rest of vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: prize winning burrito bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Mix Bisquick, water and refried beans.
Spread in pie plate.
Layer remaining ingredients on bean mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes. Serve with sour cream.

title: pizzadillas
directions: In a greased skillet on medium heat, place 1 tortilla.
Top with pepperoni cheese slices and sprinkle with mozzarella cheese then top with another tortilla.
Brown on each side and serve.

title: hot pepperoni bread
directions: Let dough rise at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a cookie sheet with oil.
Roll out the dough.
Layer pepperoni and cheese on top.
Roll it up.
Cut it in half.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Grip it to make sure it is done on both sides. Serve warm.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix milk, eggs, sugar and butter.
Add vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Crush vanilla wafers and mix with all ingredients real good.
If too dry, add a little more milk.
Butter a tube pan or Bundt pan.
Pour mix into pan and cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pretty salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice until it bubbles.
Add Jell-O and chill until it thickens.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour into pretty bowl or glass pan.

title: pumpkin-cheese soup
directions: In large
heavy
saucepan, lightly saute green onions in the butter.
Stir in flour, seasoned salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Remove from heat.
Add
milk and chicken broth.
Cook, stirring frequently.
Add
cheese, stir until melted.
Blend in pumpkin. Simmer 5 minutes, let simmer 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: oven baked catfish with pecan sauce
directions: Preheat oven to
450°.	Rinse fillets in cold water and pat dry.
Mix
cornmeal, bread crumbs, paprika, red pepper and salt. Dip fillets
in
milk,
shaking
off
excess, then into cornmeal mixture, coating well.
Place fish in single layer in greased baking pan	and
drizzle with oil.	Bake 10 minutes or until fish is	golden	brown
and
pulls apart easily with two forks at thickest point.
Serve with Pecan Sauce.

title: grandma's pink cookies
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Add raspberry jello and sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff peaks form and sugar is dissolved.
Mix in vinegar.
Fold in chocolate bits.
Drop teaspoonfuls of batter onto a cookie sheet covered with brown paper.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave cookies in for 20 minutes longer.
These also are called raspberry meringue cookies.
They are very special!

title: sue's pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in order.
Pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Drizzle melted oleo over top and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 or 1 1/2 hours or until knife tested.
Top with whipped topping.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: buckhorn inn's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and confectioners sugar together until crumbly.
Place on bottom of crust, saving 2 tablespoons to sprinkle on top.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream the butter and peanut butter.
Sift powdered sugar into mixture until pretty stiff to roll into balls.
Put balls on wax paper and put in refrigerator for a while.
Later melt chocolate chips and 1/2 bar paraffin.
Dip balls in 2/3 way so top shows peanut butter.

title: pineapple and cheese
directions: Combine sugar, flour and juice over medium heat until thin. Add pineapple chunks and cheese; stir well.
Pour into greased (or use Pam) casserole.
Top with crushed crackers.
Drizzle butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
I usually double this recipe.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all in long Pyrex baking dish.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar. Stir in 1 quart milk.
Stir until well blended.
Add vanilla. Break up bread in 1/4 pieces.
Put into milk mixture and pour melted oleo over top and sprinkle cinnamon.
Place dish in pan of water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: herbed popovers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place cast iron popover pans into oven to heat.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in milk and butter.
Add flour, basil and salt to egg mixture.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
Carefully remove hot popover pan from oven. Grease with vegetable shortening.
Divide batter into popover cups.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until puffed and firm on top. Serve immediately.
Makes 8 popovers.

title: roasted russets with garlic
directions: In a large roasting pan, toss together potatoes, olive oil, salt, pepper flakes and garlic.
Roast in 350° oven, tossing occasionally, for 1 hour.
Add parsley; toss and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt into a large bowl.
Beat eggs and sugar together in medium-size bowl, with mixer, until fluffy.
Stir in oil and applesauce.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients; stir until moistened.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Set aside in dish.
Dip fish pieces (about 2 x 3-inch or 2-inch lengths) in 1/3 cup milk.
Dredge into dry mixture.
Place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Drizzle with 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: walnut-raisin rolls
directions: Combine 1/2 cup white flour with the rye flour, yeast, sugar and salt in a large mixer bowl fitted with paddle or dough hook. At low speed, stir in hot water and butter; beat until smooth, 1 minute.
Add enough white flour, 1/2 cup at a time, to make a soft dough that begins to pull away from sides of bowl.
Stir in raisins and walnuts just to blend.
On lightly floured surface, knead dough until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in large lightly greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover with kitchen towel and let rise in a warm, draft-free place until doubled in bulk, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch dough down.
Grease cookie sheet.
Divide dough into 16 equal pieces.
Shape each into a ball and roll lightly in additional white flour.
Arrange balls 1/2-inch apart in 4 rows on cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°. Adjust oven rack to center position.
Bake rolls 30 minutes or until tops are golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 16 rolls.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown ground beef or chuck (drain off excess grease).
Chop onion; brown with beef and salt and pepper to taste.
Blend in barbecue sauce and let all of this simmer for about 15 minutes. Mix in pork and beans.
Pour all of this into medium casserole dish.
Take biscuits and cut in half.
Place around the edges of the casserole dish.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Put in a 375° oven only until cheese is melted good.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together at once.
Grease and flour a tube or
Bundt
pan.
Put
cup chopped pecans over the bottom of the pan
and
then pour in batter.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Remove
from
oven and leave in pan.
Punch holes in the top of the cake with a toothpick and pour glaze over it at once.

title: mary beth's dip
directions: Mash the cream cheese on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Spread chili over cream cheese and add green chilies over mixture, adding shredded cheese over entire mixture.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot with chips or Tostitos.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add Cool Whip, mixing on low speed until well blended.
Remove plastic lining from graham cracker crust (save plastic to invert as a cover for cheesecake).
Pour cream cheese mixture into crust.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Top with fruit or pie filling, if desired.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg and beat well. Add milk and vanilla.
Add chopped pecans and dry ingredients and mix well.
Shape in rolls and freeze.
Slice thinly and bake on greased sheet at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: dandy yams
directions: Peel and halve sweet potatoes lengthwise.
Brown in butter in skillet.
Arrange in casserole with butter; sprinkle brown sugar over yams.
Pour honey, orange juice and rind over all.
Bake, covered, at 450° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 20 minutes more.
Baste often.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in dish.
Place dish in pan of water.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Grease and flour pizza pan.
Slice cookie dough and place in pan.
Let set a few minutes and press evenly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Soften cream cheese and mix with sugar and vanilla. Spread over crust while warm.
Mix berries and glaze; spread over top and refrigerate.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Drain hominy.
Add mushroom soup, flour, butter, chopped onions, crab meat, Lea & Perrins sauce, eggs and grated cheese. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: joe's famous banana chocolate ice cream
directions: Recipe fills gallon size freezer.

title: swedish thin pancakes
directions: Beat until smooth.
Use round frypan.
Spray bottom.
Swish small amount of batter in pan.
Turn over with spatula.

title: pizza dough
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add the oil.
Mix and knead for 15 minutes.
Let rise until double in bulk or about 2 hours.
Roll out into shape.

title: hot cheese balls
directions: Melt cheese.
Cook sausage and drain.
Mix drained sausage with Bisquick, then pour cheese over and stir well.
Then make into balls.
Bake at 365° for 15 minutes.
Bakes about 70 balls. Freezes well.

title: chicken casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Heat soup; add celery, mayonnaise, onion, almonds and chicken to soup.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover with 1/4-inch stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mama's old fashion dinner rolls
directions: Warm milk.
Add sugar, margarine and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Put 2 cups flour in bowl.
Add yeast and milk mixture.
Add beaten eggs and beat.
Mix in remaining flour for a smooth, light dough.
Let dough rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Form dough into desired shape.
Place in baking pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: grandma broadway's sweet potato pone
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cool and skin.
Combine potatoes, eggs and lemon juice.
Blend until smooth.
Add sugar, blend well. Add flour and blend.
Melt margarine in large baking pan in oven. Pour melted margarine into potato mixture and blend.
Pour into pan and bake at 400° for about one hour.
Cool and slice.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy; add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Blend in sugar.
Fold in nuts and crackers.
Pack mixture into greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool and top with Cool Whip and pineapple.

title: buckeye cookies
directions: Melt butter or margarine with peanut butter.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar and Rice Krispies.
Stir, then shape into balls; chill.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler. Dip about 1/2 of each ball.
May need toothpick to dip with.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Melt caramels in milk and add nuts. Drop by spoon fulls on wax paper. Dip in melted bark.

title: spaghetti pizza lasagna
directions: Combine cooked spaghetti, milk and eggs.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread spaghetti sauce over spaghetti.
(I add 1 can of tomato soup with sauce.)
Add a layer of pepperoni next.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: texas hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and green pepper in hot fat until yellow.
Add ground beef and fry until mixture falls apart.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour, removing cover last 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 generous servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat on low speed of an electric mixer until mixed well.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill 2 hours.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add the rest of the ingredients. Spread sour cream and Cheddar cheese on top; microwave.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: chinese vegetables
directions: Slice cabbage, celery and onions diagonally.
Put vegetables in a large saucepan and add oil and water. Cover and steam for 5 minutes.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with lettuce torn into bite size pieces.
Next, add onion, then green pepper and peas. At this time, spread a light layer of mayonnaise over peas.
Cover with shredded cheese, then bacon bits.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 8 hours before serving.

title: merry heart chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss and season to taste. Add more yogurt if it is not moist enough. Serve chilled. Makes approximately 6 cups.

title: crab imperial
directions: Remove cartilage from crab meat.
In a medium saucepan, melt 1 tablespoon of the butter; mix in flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly to keep mixture smooth and free from lumps.
Cook, stirring, over medium heat, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread cubes. Let cool.
Fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Remove tops of peppers, seeds and membranes (pepper tops may be diced without seeds, stem and membranes and added to meat). *Parboil pepper cups in boiling salted water about 5 minutes. Drain.
Brown meat and onion (in oil if desired); add tomatoes, rice and Worcestershire.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer until rice is almost tender (about 5 minutes).
Add cheese. Stuff peppers; stand upright in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with more cheese.
Serves 6.

title: apple tart
directions: Mix together apples, flour, cinnamon, sugar, nuts, orange peel and lemon juice.
Place in pie shell, using top crust in a lattice effect.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When baked, brush with egg white, then top with confectioners sugar glaze.

title: shrimp-and-pasta stir-fry(low-fat)
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Combine mayonnaise and next 3 ingredients in a bowl; stir well with a wire whisk and set aside.
Coat a wok or large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add oil and place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add ginger root and garlic; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add shrimp and asparagus; stir-fry 3 minutes or until shrimp is done.
Add mayonnaise mixture and pasta; cook until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Yield:
2 servings (serving size:
1 1/2 cups). Calories 403.
Fat grams 8.2.

title: french market beigmets
directions: Heat milk to scalding stage.
Put margarine and sugar in bowl; add
milk
and
stir
until melted.
Cool and add yeast. Stir until
yeast
is dissolved.
Sift dry ingredients and add 1/2
cup milk
mixture
to form batter.
Add egg and remaining mixture. Cover
and set aside for 1 hour.
Knead gently.
Roll out
on floured
board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in diamond shapes. Deep fry at 385° and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: coconut supreme pie
directions: Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, then cool.

title: bread(four loaves)
directions: Measure all ingredients.
Follow each step carefully.
Test lukewarm water.
Dissolve sugar, salt and yeast in the quart of warm water.
Pour liquid into the 12 cups flour.
Stir until it is all mixed well.
Add shortening; stir in the dough and then knead until it is smooth and elastic to the touch.
Place dough in a bowl and let rise.
Knead again and let rise again.
Roll into four loaves.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti (broken small) according to directions.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Toss with all other ingredients.
Store overnight in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: roasted carrots with fresh rosemary
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except the carrots, and toss until well coated. On a sprayed sheet pan, lay out the carrots and roast in a 350° oven.
Roast until tender, about 20 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Place all ingredients except nuts, in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave at Medium (50%) until chocolate chips are melted (3 to 5 minutes), stirring once or twice during cooking.
Stir in the nuts.

title: frosty date balls
directions: Cream the butter and powdered sugar; add water, vanilla, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 20 minutes.
While warm, roll cookies in powdered sugar. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: green rice bake
directions: Cook the rice according to package directions.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Pour can of salmon into lightly greased baking dish.
Add tomatoes (drained), eggs and soda crackers (crushed).
Add black pepper.
Stir with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and cook 45 minutes to one hour.

title: elsa's brown sugar delights
directions: Mix well and form into small balls.
Flatten with a fork. Place 1/2 pecan on each.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Put 1 teaspoon soda into 1 cup buttermilk and add to the other ingredients.
Add flour, jam, raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° until done.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain well.
Add whipped eggs, salt, and pepper to squash and onions.
Pour mixture into greased baking dish; dot with butter.
Top with cornflake crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute squash, onion and garlic in margarine for approximately 10 minutes; add spices and mix well.
In a large bowl, beat eggs. Add 1 1/2 cups of cheese, then add squash mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate that has been lightly sprayed with cooking spray and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
About 10 minutes before it is done, sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over the top of the pie. Let it sit for about 5 minutes before cutting.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gently fold into batter.

title: sausage and macaroni creole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Fry sausage and onion; drain off grease.
Blend in flour.
Add tomatoes; stir until thick.
Add sausage and cooked macaroni.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Serves 4.

title: quick caramel sauce
directions: Combine milk and caramels in top of double boiler. Cook over hot water until caramels are melted. Serve warm or cold. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 2 cups water.
Soften cream cheese and whip with jello.
Add other ingredients and pour into mold. Makes a large salad and is very good.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Crumble cake up in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding, Cool Whip and sour cream together.
Mix glaze and strawberries together.
Cover cake with pudding mixture.
Top with strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: green bean and red bell pepper stir-fry
directions: Cook green beans in boiling salted water for 3 minutes; drain and cool with cold water.
Blot dry.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Add green beans and red pepper.
Stir-fry until crisp-tender, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soy sauce and lemon juice.

title: sandies
directions: Measure and mix well all ingredients, except powdered sugar. Hand knead until it forms a soft, well blended ball.
Pinch off small bits of dough.
Roll in hand to make balls 1/2-inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until golden brown or about 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove and coat immediately with powdered sugar.
When cool, coat again with powdered sugar.
Store in sealed container.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: homemade dough recipe
directions: In bowl, mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add oil and mix; add food coloring to water.
Add colored water and knead until smooth. If dough is too dry, add a few drops water and knead.
If dough is too soft, add small amounts of flour and knead.
Let dough cool before using.
Store in sealed container to keep soft.
Do not mix other brands of modeling compounds.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4, sweet potato pie
directions: Mix above ingredients. Pour stirred ingredients into unbaked pie shell. Cook about an hour at 350 degrees.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put this on bottom of well-greased pan.
Put chicken pieces on top of mixture.
Sprinkle top of chicken with 1/2 package dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours plus 15 minutes without uncovering.

title: low-fat pineapple pie
directions: Mix ingredients well for 1 minute and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 3 hours.

title: basil, tomato and mozzarella salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Toss and pour Italian dressing over salad. Let stand at room temperature before serving.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix cucumbers and onions in a bowl with a lid.
Cover with salt.
Shake to allow salt to coat the vegetables.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Rinse the salt off under running water.
Add approximately 2 tablespoons apple cider vinegar and 1 cup water. Mix thoroughly.
Add more or less vinegar to taste.
Serve chilled.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water; let set.
Beat, then add rest of ingredients.
Let set.

title: caramel bread
directions: Cut dough into 1/2-inch pieces.
Arrange half of pieces in a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Spoon over dough.
Top with remaining dough pieces.
Brush dough with melted butter.
Cover; let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, 1 hour or until dough has doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Serve immediately as coffee cake or dessert.

title: juicy, tasty meat loaf
directions: *A medium to heavy sprinkle of seasoned pepper, garlic pepper, Mrs. Dash, or whatever seasoning (herbs/spices) you wish to use.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, pie filling, eggs and vanilla.
Stir with spoon; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with chocolate frosting.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Blend in sugar.
Stir flour mixture into egg mixture. Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie or baking sheet.
Flatten each cookie with oiled glass dipped in sugar. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until a delicate brown.
Remove immediately from baking sheet.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Grease and flour 1 large loaf pan.
Set oven at 300°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
When creamy, fold in flour and salt.
Spoon into pan and bake about 1 1/2 hours.
Wrap tightly when completely cooled. Pound cake improves if stored a day or two.

title: pear salad
directions: Place lettuce leaves on a dish, arranging pear halves on top. Put a dab of mayonnaise on each pear.
Sprinkle cheese on pears. Place a cherry on top.
Chill and serve.

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; shape into 24 meatballs.
Brown meatballs in oil in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Remove as they brown. Combine soup and broth in a Dutch oven.
Add meatballs and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add parsley.

title: two-story lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and boiling water.
Cook until clear.
Add egg yolks and cook until thick.
Add juice of lemons, grated rind and butter.
Set aside 1 cup of filling, covered with wax paper.
Pour rest of filling into baked crust and chill.

title: 4-meats spaghetti
directions: Combine all meats and seasoning; bring to a boil for 20 minutes.
In large pot, bring spaghetti to a boil; drain.
Mix all together in large pot.
Bring to a boil for 15 minutes.
Serve. Makes four Ponderosa servings.

title: mounds(candy)
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, coconut and almond.
Drop onto waxed paper and refrigerate until firm.
Melt chips and paraffin.
Dip coconut mixture in chocolate mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chili dip
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain.
Stir in chili sauce, chili and soup.
Spoon into a 1 3/4-quart baking dish; bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: walnut hermits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, blend together butter and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add spices.
Stir in sour cream, then add walnuts, raisins and dates.
Stir well.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a cooked crust that has been cooled.
Beat 3 egg whites with 5 tablespoons sugar and cream of tartar to make meringue.
Bake in 350°
oven until lightly brown.

title: spaghetti sauce(12 servings)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in a 6-quart saucepan.
Remove bacon and all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Save both bacon and extra fat.
Add ground beef, breaking it up with a spoon.
Cook, covered, until brown, stirring occasionally.
Stir in onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add additional bacon fat, if needed. Mash plum tomatoes with a spoon.
Stir the tomatoes and tomato paste, bacon, 1 cup of wine, 4 teaspoons each of oregano and basil and all of the remaining ingredients into the sauce.
Bring to a boil and simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Taste after an hour of cooking and adjust seasoning.
Herbs vary and so do personal tastes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery.
Add crawfish tails, mushroom soup and paprika.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add Creole seasoning and onion tops.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve on white rice.

title: hot buttered rum sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, butter and cream.
Heat over low heat, stirring occasionally until hot.
Stir in extract.
Yields approximately 1 3/4 cups.

title: pork chops and kraut
directions: Boil chops 30 minutes in small amount of water.
Then add peeled whole potatoes, carrots, onions and kraut and juice; salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly (covered) 2 hours.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine
eggs and flour; beat well.
Add milk, corn and melted oleo.
Turn
into a greased casserole dish and bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: weight watchers four layered dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix margarine, salt and flour and press in pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce, melted shortening and soda together.
Add eggs, sugar and spices, while continuing to mix.
Put pecans (coarsely chopped) and raisins in flour; toss until coated.
Add to mixture, blending well.
Pour into two large greased loaf pans or 3 smaller ones.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red earth cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, cocoa, food coloring, coffee, soda and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add in flour, salt and buttermilk.
Bake in 3 greased pans at 375° until done. Cool cakes, then fill and frost with Red Earth Icing.

title: raw apple muffins(makes 16)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 16 muffin tins.
Put 3 mixing bowls out.
Mix apples and sugar in one bowl and set aside. Mix eggs, oil and vanilla in second bowl and stir to blend.
In the third bowl, put flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir and blend with fork.

title: white lily "light" biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Measure flour into bowl by spooning into measuring cup and leveling off.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until resembles coarse crumbs.
Blend in just enough milk with fork until dough leaves the sides of the bowl. (Too much milk makes dough too sticky to handle; not enough milk makes biscuits dry.)

title: hot rolls
directions: While yeast is dissolved in 1 cup warm water with sugar, combine eggs, salt, Crisco and 2 cups warm water.
Combine this mixture and add about 8 cups flour.
Let this mixture rise until doubled in bulk.
Pour out on bread board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Pinch off enough dough for amount of rolls to be used.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Cover with melted butter; fold over.
Place in greased baking pan.
Let rise until doubled in thickness.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Place remaining dough in greased covered dish.
Will keep in refrigerator 4 to 5 days.

title: broccoli bake(quick and easy quiche)
directions: Beat Bisquick, eggs, milk and minced onions for 20 strokes; spread on bottom of rectangular pan (13 x 7 x 3-inch).
Spread on dough the broccoli and garlic.
Beat together the eggs, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and Monterey Jack cheese.
Cook at 375° for approximately 1/2 hour or until eggs are set and cheese is slightly brown.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Slowly melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat and add confectioners sugar and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Return to heat. Simmer 10 minutes.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: chili-shrimp with bacon(microwave needed)
directions: Arrange frozen shrimp in circle in a 9-inch pie plate and add water. Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) for 2 minutes. Rotate plate 1/2 turn.
Microwave until almost done, 2 to 3 minutes longer. Drain.

title: chex mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In open roasting pan, melt butter in oven.
Remove.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire. Gradually add cereals, nuts and pretzels, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil water; add rice.
Cook celery and onion in oleo until tender.
Mix everything together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter marshmallow fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 8 minutes at boiling point.
Pour mixture over marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick and creamy; pour into greased pan until it cools, then cut.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/3 cubed beef.
Form into ball and roll in beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and let set 15 minutes.
Make out in balls the size of walnut.
Place on floured cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Brown ground beef until done; salt and pepper to taste.
Place 1/2 of ground beef in bottom of large casserole.
Arrange a layer of potatoes over beef, a layer of kidney beans, sprinkle (washed) rice over beans, a layer of chopped onion, salt and pepper. Repeat each layer of potatoes, beans, rice and onion.
Use other half of beef for top.
Pour tomato juice over ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until well done and breaking apart.
Drain and add other ingredients.
Mix until smooth, adding more mayonnaise or butter, if needed.

title: three bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; set aside. In a quart jar, combine the remaining ingredients.
Cover and shake thoroughly.
Pour over the other ingredients.
Mix together gently.
Chill overnight or for several hours.
Yields 6 to 8 portions.

title: vegetarian layer salad
directions: Best to show off in a wide glass bowl, but don't let that stop you!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add milk and mayonnaise. Blend until smooth.
Fold in remaining ingredients and serve with crackers or as a dip.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put hamburger in bottom of large baking pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Spread drained cans of corn, beans, peas and carrots.
Mix cans of chicken and mushroom soup and spread over vegetables.
Put Cheddar cheese soup on top and top with Tater Tots.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown pork and hamburger until it loses its color.
Cook celery 5 minutes in boiling water.
Saute celery, green pepper and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook noodles in boiling water.
Drain and add to mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in 8 x 14-inch dish at 300° to 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quail and rice dish
directions: Take a wild turkey, freshly killed, and have husband clean the breast of the turkey real good.
Halve the breast and slice real thin.
Store in freezer in freezer bags.
Take packages out as needed for meal.
Salt, pepper and flour the same as for chicken. Fry, using iron frying pan (to give it a good southern taste), until done.
Serve with wild rice and tossed salad.
Tastes better than chicken fingers.

title: date cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and milk and blend. Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt and add to mixture.
Add vanilla, dates and nuts.
Roll about 1 rounded teaspoonful of mixture into a ball, then roll in crushed corn flakes.
Place cherry on top and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: munchy crunchy cookies
directions: Beat sugars, oil and margarine until fluffy; add egg, vanilla and milk and continue beating.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar and mix well.
Stir in oats, Rice Krispies, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until barely brown. These are very crisp and melt in your mouth, but do not overbake.

title: nuts and bolts snack mix
directions: Can add any other cereal or mixed nuts of your choice.

title: sausage soup
directions: Fry sausage and bacon until done.
Place onions, garlic, kale, boullion cubes and potatoes in 1 quart of water and boil until potatoes are cooked.
Add sausage and crumbled bacon and boil with heavy cream for 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef into baking dish.
Add minced onion, salt and pepper.
Spread the soup on top of beef mixture.
Layer cheese slices on top, followed by a layer of Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Place roux in 4-quart casserole.
Add hot water (mix well), salt, pepper and shrimp.
Microwave on High for 16 minutes.
Stir at 5 minute intervals.
Sprinkle onion tops on gumbo before serving over rice.
Serve file separately.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well and top with grated cheese or Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Bake in 9-inch Pyrex dish at 325° until slightly brown.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
Mix rice, soup and water.
Put in baking dish.
Arrange chops on top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Bake one hour at 300°.
You may put marshmallows on top, if desired.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed. Combine noodles, ham, onion, bell pepper, celery and mayonnaise.
Add pimento last after stirring up the other ingredients. Blend well. Blend soup, milk, cheese, black pepper and poppy seed.
Add to noodle mixture.
Put in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish. Top with Ritz crackers (crushed) and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread slices, butter both sides.
Use 8 slices to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with ham, then cheese.
Cover with remaining bread.
Combine eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Beat well, pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake cake in a jellyroll pan.
Add 1 1/4 cups milk slowly to flour.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Mix with thickened flour and milk mixture until smooth.
Spread on cake and refrigerate.

title: mom's garlic pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers in fours; line up in jar.
Put garlic on bottom.

title: chicken ole
directions: Lightly grease sides and bottom of crock-pot or large casserole dish.
Arrange alternate layers of tortillas with a mixture of chicken, soups, salsa, sour cream and onion.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and onions.
Mix together in bowl with raisins and sunflower seeds.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Brown ribs well.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over ribs.
Bake in heavy pan at 350° for 2 hours or more.
Baste 2 or 3 times during baking.

title: jo regis' lime salad
directions: Use juice from large can of fruit cocktail and enough boiling water to make 4 cups liquid.
Dissolve the jello in this liquid. Cool and when ready to jell, add the rest of the ingredients.

title: roast chicken
directions: Remove giblets.
Wash inside and out.
Save the weight label on the chicken.
Pass the spit through the chicken, from opening in the back through the cavity and out through the breast.
Use wire or string to fasten chicken securely to the spit so it turns with the spit.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover the breast with bacon, using some aluminum nails to hold the bacon.
Wrap bacon around upper parts of leg, using nails here, too.
Place spit about 12-inches over coals for any more than 15 minutes at a time.
If legs or breast start to dry out, spread with butter.
Chicken s finished when meat breaks away from bones easily.
Test one leg.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: Cut up bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in a Dutch oven until crisp and golden.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Set aside.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Then mix in oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and raisins.
Mix well and drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute pepper, celery and onions in butter until tender.
Stir in chicken and mushroom soup.
Cook spaghetti in chicken stock until tender.
Mix cooked spaghetti with chicken mixture.
Place in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until light.
Add flour and baking powder.
Fold in nuts, raisins and apples.
Grease and flour pan (I have used just Pam spray).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: dilly beans
directions: Snip the ends off whole green beans.
Wash and drop beans in boiling water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pack in sterilized pint jars and add red pepper, garlic and head of dill.
Then heat cider vinegar, water and salt to boiling and pour over beans.
Seal jars Makes 3 pints.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and soda.
Add milk, eggs, corn and oil. Add cheese.
Chop onion
and peppers; add to mixture and stir well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Mix all together and add enough beer to make the batter thin. Dip onion rings into batter and deep fry until golden brown.

title: thanksgiving tomorrow
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, adding turkey broth or water if mixture is too dry (I use turkey gravy if any left).
Place in lightly greased
1-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until hot and lightly brown on top. Garnish with cranberry jelly or sauce if desired.

title: chicken with duck sauce
directions: Put chicken in roasting pan (13 x 9-inch); leave uncovered. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: caramels
directions: Put in
a large pan.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes after it starts to boil.
Pour onto greased pan.
Let cool 24 hours.
Cut and wrap in waxed paper.
Store in cool area.
Yields about 2 pounds.

title: cranberry cheese salad
directions: Stir Jell-O into hot water until dissolved. Add cold water. Refrigerate 2 cups liquid until thickened.

Reserve 1 cup at room temperature. Stir the cream cheese into this cup until smooth. Oil mold and pour cream cheese mixture in. Chill. When the 2 cups Jell-O are thickened, chop the apple and add to Jell-O along with the cranberry sauce.
Pour into mold over cream cheese mixture and re-chill.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Sift flour with soda, twice.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add sour cream.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cashew and carrot soup
directions: Melt butter and oil in a soup pot; saute onions for 1 minute. Stir in carrots; saute until onions are soft (orange).
Stir in tomato paste, apples, stock and salt.
Bring to boil; stir in rice.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Remove 1 cup and blend. Return to pot.
Add raisins, cashews and honey; bring to boil again.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add milk and heat through.
May be served hot or cold with a dob of yogurt.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix together egg, cheese, stuffing and butter.
