Combine with spinach and put into casserole. Sprinkle 1/4 cup shredded sharp cheese over top and bake 20 minutes in 350° oven or until nicely browned.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion in large saucepan until onions are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: italian parmesan chicken
directions: In a food processor, process Special K, Parmesan cheese, flour and Italian seasoning until cereal resembles fine crumbs. Pour salad dressing in another bowl. Dip chicken in salad dressing. Coat with cereal mixture. Place in shallow baking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until tender. Do not cover or turn chicken while baking.

title: meatbread
directions: Follow instructions for the hot roll mix; divide into two parts and let rise.
Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain.
Add cheese and cook until melted.
Roll out dough; put 1/2 of meat and cheese mixture in each piece of dough and roll up.
Cook at 375° until golden brown.

title: beef stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook green pepper halves in boiling water 3 to 5 minutes. Drain well.
Combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup catsup and pepper halves.
Pack approximately 1/2 cup of meat mixture in each pepper half.
Top with 2 tablespoons catsup for each half.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: sausage and cheddar quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish with pastry.
Trim excess pastry around edges.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Prick the shell and bake 5 more minutes.

title: comfort egg nog
directions: Chill liquids before mixing.
Separate egg whites and yolks. Beat yolks and add sugar.
Stir in whipped cream, milk, cream and Southern Comfort.
Beat egg whites; fold in.
Dust with nutmeg. Chill.
Makes 10 servings.

title: lindsay nut bread
directions: Beat eggs; stir in milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Spray 2 loaf pans with Pam.
Place mix in pans; let stand for 15 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Can be frozen for later.

title: peach cobbler
directions: *If using fresh fruit, sweeten to taste and add 1/2 cup milk.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well. If large, cut into thick slices. Steam for about 7 minutes or until firm but slightly tender. Pour oil into casserole dish. Add steamed potatoes, garlic, shallot, salt and pepper.
Toss to mix well. Bake uncovered in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir a couple of times during baking so potatoes cook evenly.

title: beef macaroni casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and turn into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen raspberry pie
directions: Beat sugar into egg whites until stiff.
Fold in raspberries, Cool Whip, lemon juice and dash of salt.
Fold into baked pie shells.
Top with almonds and freeze.
Set out a few minutes before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sweet and sour rabbit or chicken
directions: Stir the dressing and preserves together and sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Stir until blended.
Pour over chicken and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a 350° oven.
Serve over rice.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Wash chicken and place in shallow dish.
Mix ingredients for sauce and pour half over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn chicken and add rest of sauce.
Bake about 30 minutes more. Serves 4 to 5.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will need the following equipment:
8 to 10 paper or plastic cups (8-ounce) and decorations for dirt (gummy worms, bugs or anything you wish).

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and eggs together. Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, nuts and coconut, mixing well together.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 40 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
When done, immediately spread marshmallows over the hot cake.
Let cool and frost with Icing.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar; add eggs and vanilla. Fold in sour cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Turn the oven off and leave the cheesecake in the oven for another 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool. Add topping of your choice (suggest Comstock).

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef tenderloin across grain into strips, each about 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch.
Cook and stir beef in margarine in 10-inch skillet over low heat until brown.
Reserve 1/3 cup of the broth.
Stir remaining broth, the ketchup, salt and garlic into skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients with 1 cup of water in large bowl. Beat for 5 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and dust with powdered sugar.

title: corn pudding(not a dessert)
directions: Saute chiles in butter. Cool and add remaining ingredients. Put in buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add boiling water while stirring constantly.
Cook until thick in double boiler.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook about 2 minutes longer.
Add lemon juice and rinds and cook until thick.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell. Cover with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes until brown.

title: quick and easy chicken with rice
directions: Sprinkle rice in bottom of 3 to 4-quart casserole.
Place on rice.
Mix together soup, water and soup mix and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 40 minutes at 400°, then bake about 20 minutes at 300°.
If a bit dry when finished, add 1/2 cup water and replace cover for a few minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Add cocoa to sugar and mix well.
Stir in 2 cups milk to make a smooth mixture and heat in top of a double boiler.
Beat egg yolks; add flour, blended with remaining 1/2 cup milk.
Add salt and stir into milk mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pastry shell.
Top with meringue made of the egg whites and 8 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° until meringue is lightly browned.
Yield: One 9-inch pie.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add soda to flour and sift mixture 3 times.
Add alternately, flour and sour cream to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon lemon flavoring. Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 to 2 hours.
Let stand 15 minutes before taking out of pan.
The longer you keep this cake, the more moist it becomes.

title: patty's turkey dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve immediately.

title: punch
directions: Mix frozen lemon juice with 1 quart water.
Slice bananas. Mix all juices and bananas, then chill.
When punch is ready to serve, add ginger ale and sherbet.
Color to suit the occasion.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery.
Add tomato soup (undiluted) and creamed corn.
Cook shell macaroni; drain.
Add to meat mixture. Place into casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: ft. ontario molasses drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat in.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend alternately with molasses and sour milk.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Chill.

title: crab-parsley "pizza appetizer"
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix in small amount of onion.
Add small amount of milk until spreadable.
Spread over bottom of shallow platter.
Cut crab in bite-sized pieces; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
At serving time, spread on cocktail sauce.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley to resemble "pizza."
Serve with crackers for guests to spread with appetizer.
This will disappear!!!
(With a large group, you can double or triple recipe.)

title: cabbage and bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in large pan in cold water to cover.
Soak 6 hours; drain.
In same pot, combine beans, ham hock, garlic, onion and 8 cups of water.
Bring to boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop into hot skillet and fry until crisp.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Brown crumbled sausage; drain.
Place in bottom of pie shells. (If you use crescent rolls, place in a 13 x 9-inch pan and pinch together to form crust.)
Sprinkle cheese on top of sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour on top of sausage.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until eggs are set and slightly browned.
I make on Christmas Eve and refrigerate and bake for Christmas morning.

title: sweet potatoes flambe
directions: Mix sugar, water, orange rind and butter in heavy skillet. Heat until butter and sugar are melted. Add potatoes and cook over low heat, turning occasionally until potatoes are candied.

title: 10 minute peanut brittle
directions: A normal pizza on top, and a beautiful egg and cheese crust, with flecks of green and a slight crunch.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs together.
Add sugar, syrup, butter, vanilla and nuts.
Stir these together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Delicious topped with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in saucepan. Gradually add milk. Cook over medium heat until thickened. (Add more milk if too thick.) Add vanilla. Serve over hot biscuits with butter. Kids love this as a special treat for breakfast.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Steep the tea in one cup of boiling water for about 2 minutes. Add the sugar and stir until dissolved. Add the juice, lemonade, water and bourbon. Pour into a container and freeze 12 hours or overnight. This keeps in the freezer for several month. Scoop to serve and splash with a little 7-Up or Sprite.

title: hot soup
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey.
Add rest of the ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender.
(The meat can be omitted and chopped basil and small, cooked pasta can be added before serving.)
Garnish with a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese.
Serve with crusty bread for a complete meal.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: windfall cake
directions: Grease deep cake tin or tube pan.
Sift flour with salt into bowl and rub in the margarine or butter (I use butter).
Stir in the sugar, raisins and apples.
Stir in the eggs with a spoon.
Do not beat.
Put mixture into the prepared cake pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 minutes, until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serve warm from the oven, dredged with powdered sugar.
Serves 8.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry sausage (taken out of casings) and add garlic and Italian seasonings, if desired.
Drain well.
Mix the beaten egg with parsley and then add the shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Roll out the dough, length longer than width, in a rectangle shape.
Mix the sausage in with cheese and egg mixture.
Put in the middle of the dough and spread it out, leaving about 1/2-inch around the edges. Roll the dough up and put in a bread pan (greased).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Good luck!

title: arroz con pollo
directions: In a small bowl, combine salt, pepper, garlic, oregano and chili powder.

Sprinkle spices over both sides of chicken pieces. Place chicken in slow cooker. Pour broth and wine over chicken. Cover and cook on low 5 to 6 hours. Remove chicken and cover to keep warm. Turn control to high. Add peas. Cover and cook on high for 7 to 10 minutes. Stir in cooked rice and chicken until combined. Sprinkle with cilantro and serve.

title: fruit 'n juice breakfast shake
directions: Break banana into small pieces and put into the blender with pineapple juice, yogurt and strawberries. Secure lid and blend until smooth. Divide shake between 2 glasses and serve immediately.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; take out stems and dice.
Place in frying pan with onions and butter to soften.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add breadcrumbs to absorb the butter in the frying pan.
Fill mushroom caps.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Boil together 1 cup white vinegar, 1/2 cup water and 2 cups sugar.
Add to this 1 teaspoon celery seed and 1 teaspoon mustard seed.
Let cool.
Shred cabbage; add 1 tablespoon salt and mix well.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out all liquid.
Then add to cabbage 1 grated carrot, 1 bell pepper (finely chopped) and 1 small onion (finely chopped).
Pour cooled vinegar mixture over this.
Freeze in containers you would want to use one at a time.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cook in small amount of water until tender; drain.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon crumbs in greased 2-quart casserole. Combine sour cream, salad dressing, flour and onions; blend thoroughly.
Place layer of potatoes in casserole, salt and pepper to taste.
Top with half the egg slices.
Spread with half the cream mixture.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle remaining 2 tablespoons bread crumbs on top.
Pour melted butter evenly over top.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: waffles
directions: Mix eggs with buttermilk and shortening.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Grease waffle iron well.

title: tuna tater casserole
directions: Combine tuna fish, potatoes, onion and soup in a casserole. Mix well. Sprinkle bread crumbs evenly on top.
Pour melted butter or margarine evenly on top. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice with a little butter. Add 2 cups milk and the raisins.
Place remainder of milk in bowl with eggs, sugar and salt.
Add vanilla.
Mix with rice.
Before baking, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown and set.

title: peanut-coconut-jewels
directions: Mix peanut butter with honey and raisins.
Spread coconut on waxed paper.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper; roll in coconut to completely cover.
Chill and serve.

title: salt pork
directions: Select dry salt jowl reasonably thick with woven lean strips across the center.
Slice to medium thick slices.
Add water to skillet to cover meat slices.
To the water add sugar.
Boil about 5 minutes; drain and cook until a golden brown.
This is better if not cooked until crisp.

title: easy hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Reserve some almonds to sprinkle on top before baking.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Whip together eggs, flour, sugar, butter, corn and milk.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° until firm.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Outside will be firm before center.
Stir once when edges have firmed before topping with crumbs.
Serves 6.

title: clam sauce and shells
directions: Cook shells as directed on box.
In large saucepan, cook onions and garlic in olive oil until tender.
Stir into spaghetti sauce; add reserved liquid.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add clams; heat through.
Serve over shells.
Parmesan cheese for garnish.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: spam baked hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In medium bowl, combine bacon, green pepper and onion. Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until bacon is brown, stirring once.
Add ground beef, rice, milk, egg, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Shape into balls and arrange in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: crock-pot hungarian goulash
directions: Put steak cubes, onion and garlic in crock-pot. Stir in flour to coat steak. Add remaining ingredients, EXCEPT sour cream. Cook on low 7 to 10 hours or high 4 hours. Add sour cream 30 minutes before serving. Serving over noodles.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add all other ingredients.
Add juice from cans, also.
Simmer and serve.

title: pear relish
directions: Core, peel and grind pears through coarse food chopper and drain until excess juice is removed.
Grind peppers and onions. Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil and boil 20 minutes.
Pack into containers.
Process in a boiling water bath canner for 10 minutes.

title: forcaccia(italian oven bread)
directions: Put flour on counter.
Make a well, add lukewarm water from the 2 cups.
Sprinkle yeast, sugar and salt in the well.
After bubbles are created, start mixing water and flour.
Use hands or mixer.
When dough is mushy, add potatoes and knead.
Put mushy dough in oiled pan (13 x 9 x 2 1/4-inches) and put in oven to double.
When doubled, heat oven to 350°.

title: classic dill dip
directions: Blend well.
Store cold for two or three hours before serving.

title: sixty second cookies
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, cocoa, butter and milk and boil 2 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter, quick oats and vanilla.
Stir well.
Spoon out on waxed paper quickly.
Mixture will thicken rapidly.
Let cool and serve.

title: mississippi sin
directions: Hollow out bread and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and put into the hollowed out bread and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with crackers, chips and cut out bread center.

title: strawberry champagne sorbet* * * * *
directions: The recipe for Coq Au Vin is a take off on the traditional French chicken.
Originally it was for a chafing dish, but, for me, it is easier to finish in the oven and enjoy my guests.
It is very rich, as most really good things are.

title: b~b~q spare ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients in advance, except meat. Keep at room temperature. Heat oven to 425°. Cover meat with garlic, salt and pepper. Place in a large shallow pan (a single layer pan is best). Cook 1/2 hour each side. Pour off grease. Lower oven to 350°. Pour sauce over meat and cook for 1 to 1-1/2 hours until meat is tender. Serves 6.

title: sausage bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well, pour into 9 x 13 pan, sprayed with cooking spray, and bake at 350° until well browned; about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Stir together soups and sour cream.
Add chicken.
Pour chicken mixture into pan.
Cover with cracker crumbs and pour melted butter over and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Cook until crackers are golden brown.

title: tappy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save liquid). Mix pineapple and marshmallows. Place in covered bowl; let set in refrigerator overnight. Mix juice from pineapple, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar; cook over medium heat until pudding like consistency. Refrigerate overnight. Next day, add apples and peanuts to both mixtures. Stir well. Add Cool Whip and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together the Tang, pudding and fruit juice.
Beat until thick.
Add the fruits.
Beat until well mixed.

title: orange honey bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add to eggs the orange juice, melted shortening and candied orange peel. Combine dry ingredients with the egg mixture, just enough to moisten flour.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn, cabbage and peppers real fine.
Put everything in a pot.
Boil 20 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: deviled ham dip or sandwich spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or melba toast rounds or bread.
May be made a day or two ahead of time.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix and spread in bottom of 8 x 18 x 2-inch Corning Ware dish; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Pour 8 ounce bottle of Zesty Italian dressing over all.
Let stand for 2 hours, then serve.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Boil syrup and 2/3 cup sugar until it spins a thread.
Add 1 cup strawberries.
Boil 5 minutes and set off fire until boiling stops.
Add 1 cup sugar and remaining strawberries.
Seal in jars.

title: tony's deer roast
directions: In a large bowl, coat deer with tenderizer.
Add Worcestershire, wine, onions, half the celery and water.
Cover and marinate overnight.
Turn once or twice.

title: dress up dressing
directions: Place biscuits and cornbread in large bowl.
Cook celery and onions in chicken broth 5 minutes.
Pour this over crumbs; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients in given order.
Pour in large 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased baking pan or dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add crushed potato chips and pecans.
Stir in flour.
Form into small balls, about 1 tablespoon of dough for each.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Press balls flat with bottom of a tumbler dipped in sugar.
Place pecan half on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes, until cookies are lightly browned.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt candy bars in double boiler.
Add Hershey's syrup.
Cool. Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients along with buttermilk, then add chocolate mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour or until done. Top with ice cream and fudge topping.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine strawberries, apples and Mandarin oranges.
Add marshmallows, stir together.
Fold in sour cream and coconut until mixed.

title: southern cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling, salted water for 3 to 5 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Add egg, cheese and butter.
Stir until cheese melts.
Turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir in pie filling. Pour into greased and floured 9 X 13 pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: cappuccino cheesecake
directions: Note:
Best if made 1 day in advance to chill firmly.

title: mushroom risotto(makes 6 large servings)
directions: Spray large saucepan with cooking spray.
Cook mushrooms and onions over medium heat about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until onions are tender.
Stir in rice.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in apple juice and 2 cups of the broth.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to medium.
Cook, uncovered, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Stir in 1 cup of broth; cook, uncovered, until most liquid is absorbed. Repeat this process, 1 cup of broth at a time, until rice is tender and mixture is slightly thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk, cocoa and vanilla.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes and 3 seconds.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and nuts.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper to cool.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together well, flour, sugar, eggs, soda, vanilla and pineapple.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve inside round loaf of rye or pumpernickel.
(I cut a small round slice off the top to use as a lid.
Then scoop out the bread in a bowl shape.
Use leftover chunks to dip.)

title: appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use as a filling between lightly buttered slices of sandwich bread.
Trim crust if desired.
Cut each sandwich diagonally in 4 triangles.
Makes 2/3 cup filling.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar and shortening.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in oats, coconut, raisins and milk.
In small mixing bowl, sift together flour, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda. Stir in oat mixture.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown; let cool.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, garlic salt, pepper, paprika and poultry seasoning in a plastic or paper bag.
Shake chicken pieces in seasoned flour.
Combine milk and egg.
Dip chicken pieces in milk mixture.
Shake chicken pieces a second time in seasoned flour to coat thoroughly and evenly.
Melt Crisco in skillet to about 1/2 to 1 inch in depth.
Heat to 365°.
Brown chicken on all sides. Reduce heat to 275° and continue cooking until chicken is tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not cover.
Turn chicken several times during cooking.

title: chafing dish lobster dip
directions: Melt cream cheese over low heat very slowly.
Blend in all the ingredients except the lobster and Sauterne.
Mix well, never allowing to boil.
Add lobster and wine.
Mix and heat through. Transfer to a chafing dish.
Carefully control heat, as it will separate if it boils.
Serve with crackers or bread.
Recipe will feed several.

title: moist & fruity muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in large - I MEAN REALLY BIG - mixing bowl, beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Let the mix rest for about 10 minutes.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 16 to 18 minutes. Batter keeps up to 3 weeks refrigerated, if tightly covered. However, don't stir it each time you make a batch.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan cook onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Combine with chicken and green chillies in large bowl; set aside.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix garlic salt, pepper, onion powder, mayonnaise, lemon juice, shrimp, and cream cheese well and put on a plate.
Form into a ball, then cover with pecan pieces if desired.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl with seal.
Refrigerate.
Can keep for 2 to 3 days.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans; slice onion.
Mix in salad dressing.
Let stand several hours.
Feeds 18 to 24.

title: reuben appetizers
directions: Combine cream cheese and onion. Add sauerkraut, corned beef, and 1/4 c. bread crumbs; mix well. Shape into 1 inch balls, roll in flour, dip in milk then into the remaining 3/4 c. bread crumbs. Pour salad oil into fryer to depth of two inches. Fry in hot oil for 1-2 minutes or until brown.
These can be made ahead and reheated. Makes about 50 appetizers.

title: frieda's coleslaw
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil.
Pour over coleslaw.
May be stored in refrigerator for at least 2 weeks.

title: party punch
directions: Have all ingredients chilled.
Place in large bowl with ice rings.
Ginger ale and sherbet are needed just before serving. Serves 60.

title: strawberry lemon squares
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 c. sugar, and butter until blended. Press into bottom of 13 x 9 inch baking pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and put in baking dish.
Combine milk, soup, salt, pepper and pimento and mix with beans.
Add 1/2 can of onions. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with 1/2 can of onions and bake 5 minutes.

title: pop-oven pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook and drain meat. Add tomato sauce, 2 tablespoons flour, oregano and salt.
Heat to boiling and cook 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased baking dish and cover with Mozzarella cheese.

title: strawberry tabox cake
directions: Crush wafers fine and put more than half in bottom of 18 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Cream butter and mix with sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat well.
Spread over crumbs in pan, then cover with sliced strawberries.
Spread whipped cream over berries and cover with remaining crumbs.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and serve with or without whipped cream and strawberry on top.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Drain and save juice from pineapple.
Dissolve jello in boiling water, add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add strawberry drink and chill slightly.
Add fruit and chill until firm.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Add all ingredients and beat well.
With spoon, drop mixture in a hot pan with oil and spread mixture as thin as possible.
Fry on both sides to a golden brown.

title: mexican beef-stir-fry
directions: Cut steak into 1/8-inch slices.
Combine oil, cumin, garlic salt and oregano.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil mixture in large, nonstick frying pan until hot.
Add red pepper and onion; stir-fry over medium-high heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Stir-fry beef strips (1/2 at a time) in remaining oil mixture 1 to 2 minutes.
Return vegetables to frying pan and heat through.
Serve in soft taco shells with lettuce, cheese and salsa.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots not quite done.
Mix other ingredients in a blender.
Drain carrots and pour mixture over carrots.
Alternate layers of carrots, pepper and onion.
Let stand overnight.
Will keep, refrigerated, for weeks.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Blend ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Separate frozen roll dough into pieces (each cloverleaf makes 3 pieces).
Other rolls will work but with larger pieces of dough, use only 20; more may be too many for your pan.

title: batons sales biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients adding the flour until the dough becomes easy to knead.
Once kneaded, roll in sticks or little circles. (You can shape into the forms you like.)
Bake at 300° until golden.
When they cool, store them in tight containers for they keep a long time.

title: mama's city chicken
directions: Place meat cubes on skewers, alternating veal and pork.
Beat eggs; set aside.
Salt and pepper meat; dip in eggs, then cover with bread crumbs.
Brown in skillet, turning only once.
Remove and place in Dutch oven.
Heat soup; pour over meat.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: green grape salad
directions: Combine grapes, apples, celery and walnuts in medium bowl. Toss gently to combine.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix soup and milk. Pour into bottom of casserole and add chicken.
Mix melted butter and broth; stir into dressing.
Spoon over chicken and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbles appear at side of dish.
Freezes well.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine butter, sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and milk and beat with electric mixer.
Spread on bottom of greased 10 x 6-inch pan.
Combine 1 cup berries and water; mash and strain.
Add water to make 1 cup juice.
Set aside.
Sprinkle 3 cups berries over batter, then sugar.
Pour juice over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (preheat oven).
Serve warm.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add cocoa, eggs, vanilla, baking powder and salt, then add flour and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Frost, if desired.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: In lightly greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan, layer the ingredients in the order given.
Spread cake batter over the layered ingredients, making sure to completely cover ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, until cake tests done.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven, brown roast over medium heat.
Add dry soup mix blended with 2 1/4 cups water.
Simmer covered, turning occasionally for about 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Can also use roasting pan and cover with foil.
Roast in 350° oven for 2 hours or until tender.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans. Press into dish and bake for 10 to 20 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan and simmer, mixing well while rice or noodles are cooking.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes and serve over rice or noodles.

title: kifflings
directions: Add nuts to flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and nuts (mix quickly).
Add vanilla.
Bake on a greased and lightly floured cookie sheet in the shape of 1-inch balls.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.
Roll again when cold.

title: layered salad
directions: In 13x9 inch glass dish, layer ingredients one at a time, each in a separate layer.
Do not toss.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour and baking soda. Mix in nuts and chips. Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° 8-10 minutes.

title: macaroni soup
directions: Cook macaroni, drain, then add corn, tomato soup and cut onion.
Add the browned hamburger meat, celery, salt and pepper. Cook on slow heat for 20 minutes.

title: beets in honey sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch and salt.
Blend in water; add vinegar, honey and butter.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly until thickened. Add sauce to beets.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Beat cherries until smashed.
Add cake mix, eggs and flavoring.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Then, blend in shortening. Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add to buttermilk.
Add this mixture to the flour mixture; blend well.

title: cherry-pecan balls
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar gradually.
Add flour, cherries and pecans, water and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Roll in powdered sugar; cool and roll again in sugar.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and cocoa alternately with milk until thoroughly mixed.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Fix Dream Whip according to directions.
Drain cocktail and pineapple.
Slice bananas and add all ingredients together. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: clay dough
directions: Sift dry ingredients into heavy aluminum pan, mix liquid. Blend well.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until dough pulls away from pan or until it forms a soft ball in center of pan.
Store in Ziploc bag.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon and set aside.
In
a saucepan, place the water, cocoa, vegetable oil and butter and
bring
to
a boil.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well and
set
aside.
Mix
together eggs and buttermilk; add to batter.
Pour
into
a
greased
and
floured
9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil together for 2 minutes.
Put flour in another bowl; add soda, salt, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Set aside.
Chop nuts first and apples.
Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with chopped apples.
Add nuts.
Pour into a tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Grease and flour pan good before pouring mixture in.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add milk all at once.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly, about 1 minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.

title: chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, put meat, onions and green pepper.
Cook until meat is brown and pepper and onions are tender.
Add chili beans, tomato soup and chili powder.
Let simmer for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cheese topper
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup, sour cream and mustard.
Add broccoli.
Heat through.
Serve over potatoes.

title: cornish game hens with rice and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rub hens with olive oil, thyme, salt and pepper.

Place in an oiled roaster. Cover and put in the oven. After 30 minutes, add the parsley, mushrooms and zucchini to the pan drippings and stir to coat. Cover and return to oven for 5 minutes. Add rice, 2 cups of stock or water and bay leaves.
Add additional salt and pepper to season rice, if needed.
Continue baking for about 30 minutes more.
Hens are done when golden brown and the wings separate from the body. Remove hens and rice to serving platter and garnish with fresh parsley. Serves 8.

title: sausage stuffed baked apples
directions: Wash apples; drain, core and slice off tops.
Scoop out pulp, reserving pulp and leaving 1-inch shell.
Cook sausage; drain off excess fat.
Add onion.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add meat to reserved apple pulp and crackers.
Season with salt and pepper; mix in egg.
Stuff mixture into apple shells.
Place in buttered pan; bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add nuts, oil, eggs and berries.
Stir until moist.
Pour in greased pans.
Bake at 350°.
I bake in mini loaf pans and use 7 pans.

title: anise apple salad
directions: Toss apples and pineapple in large bowl.
In separate bowl add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over apples and pineapple, toss to cover the fruit well, serve chilled.

title: bubbles bubbles!!!
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store overnight in the refrigerator.
Then blow, blow, blow.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Combine orange juice, orange rind and egg; pour all at once into dry ingredients, mixing just enough to dampen. Carefully fold in nuts and cranberries. Spoon into greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3 inches). Spread corners and sides slightly higher than center. Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Remove from pan after cooling.

title: rolls
directions: Beat the egg; add salt, sugar and oil.
Dissolve the yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add to first mixture.
Add 1 cup warm water. Add flour until medium dough.
Knead until double in bulk.
Shape into rolls.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: cheryl's carrot cake
directions: Stir together sugar, salad oil, and eggs. Sift together cake flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, and salt separately. Combine the two ingredients together and fold in the carrots and chopped nuts. Bake at 300° for 35-40 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate squares
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in next 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Press mixture in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread melted chocolate chips on top.
Chill 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: corn meal cookies
directions: Mix fat and sugar in large bowl.
Add egg; beat well.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Drop dough from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) until lightly browned.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan.
Press rolls to form a pizza crust in pizza pan.
Add cooked sausage, hash browns, onion and cheese.
Mix together eggs, mustard and milk.
Pour on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and put into a large bowl. Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread on top.
Top with grated cheese, cover and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours.
Toss at serving time.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mix all.
Chill and serve with chips or use as a condiment for tacos or fajitas.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Combine other ingredients and mix well.
Roll into bite-sized small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Store in plastic bags.
Bake frozen 10 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and flour and mix well.
Add vanilla and buttermilk last.
Bake in unbaked pie shell 35 - 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: polish poppy seed bread
directions: Combine the yeast and 2 cups of the flour in a large mixing bowl.
Heat the milk, butter, sugar, cardamon, lemon zest and salt in a saucepan until warm, stirring to melt the butter.
Add the milk mixture and the eggs to the yeast flour.
Beat at low speed for 30 seconds, scraping the bowl constantly.
Increase the speed to high and beat 3 minutes longer.
Stir in enough of the remaining flour by hand to make a moderately stiff dough.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup to boiling in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Blend well.
Add Special K. Press mixture down firmly into a cake pan.
Melt both kinds of chips and milk.
Blend and pour over Special K mix.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: fabulous fig-preserve cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Bundt pan with nonstick spray. Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl expect pecans.
Beat until well blended.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into pan.
Bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Top with Buttermilk Glaze.

title: basic corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift together corn meal, flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Combine egg and buttermilk; add dry ingredients and stir to combine.
Heat butter in a 10-inch ovenproof skillet over moderate heat until bubbly.
Tilt to coat the pan; pour in the batter.
Cook bread on stove for about 3 minutes to give it a good crust.
Put the skillet in the oven to bake until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn the corn bread out on a rack so it doesn't get soggy as it cools.

title: toasted finger rolls
directions: Remove crust from bread and cut into 3 equal strips; spread with undiluted mushroom soup.
Do not use heavily.
Roll up bread and fasten 1/2 slice bacon with toothpick around roll.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° until brown, about 35 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Cook, drain and rinse in cold water.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done and debone.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix together soup and sour cream in casserole dish.
Add meat and stir well.
Top with crushed crackers and pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl, sift together sugar, flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
Dissolve soda in hot water, add along with the remaining ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes either by hand or at medium speed with mixer.
Batter will be thin.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Use 9 x 12-inch pan or one 9 x 9-inch pan and 12 cupcakes.

title: cheese cake dreams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch pan.
In a small bowl, mix the first 3 ingredients.
Stir in butter until well combined. Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs.
Pat remaining ingredients gently into pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: "mrs. jones' famous german oatmeal cookies by reathe morgan"
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to above mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts, oatmeal, coconut and dates.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: 8 dozen cookies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a medium sauce pan, combine sugar, milk, butter, and cocoa; bring to a boil and cook for one and one half minutes. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter, oats and vanilla.	Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper; let cool until hardened.

title: hot rolls *
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and salt with boiling water.
Cool until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to cooled mixture.
Add eggs, beat in 6 cups flour.
Stir in remaining flour by hand.
Let rise until double, punch down.
Roll out dough on floured surface, cut and fold over.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, brush with melted butter and let rise.
Bake at 400° to 425° about 10 to 15 minutes.
May be baked until half done, then frozen.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: vegetable pizza(child's recipe)
directions: Pat crescent rolls in jelly roll pan and bake according to directions on package.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Hidden Valley dry salad dressing.
Spread on cool crust.
Distribute vegetables on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cut in small pieces and serve.

title: chicken risotto
directions: In 10-inch skillet brown chicken about 15 minutes.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons oil and remove chicken.
Add rice, onion and seasonings and cook until rice is browned.
Add mushrooms, carrots and water.
Put chicken on top.
Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Make hollow in middle and add the buttermilk.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Make into a flat round with an X on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Excellent breakfast bread.

title: crisp bread and butter sliced pickles
directions: Combine pickles, onion, green peppers and whole garlic cloves. Add salt and cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand for 3 hours; drain well.
Remove garlic.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup water.
Mix all ingredients, except 7-Up, in gallon of water.
Freeze.
Six hours later, chop up mix and refreeze.
It will make a slushy mix.
Pour in punch bowl with 7-Up.
Also works well using lemon and lime instead of raspberry and strawberry.

title: jello cake
directions: Preheat oven as directed on cake mix.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed until fluffy lemon color (5 minutes). Beat in sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Set aside.
In separate bowl combine flour, ginger, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add to egg mixture.
Grease and flour large cookie sheet. Pour batter on cookie sheet (batter will be thin).
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn out on towel, sprinkled with powdered sugar and roll using towel's long edges.
Cool.
Prepare filling.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown
sausage; crumble and drain.
Saute celery, pepper and onion
in sausage grease.
Bring 3 1/2 cups water to boil; put
in rice, soup mix and bouillon.
Cook until rice is done. Combine all
ingredients;
place in casserole dish and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Mix in pot and simmer together slowly.

title: barbecued meat and egg roll
directions: Soak beef for 30 minutes in mixture of shoyu, sugar, garlic, ginger and ajinomoto.
Peel hard-cooked eggs and wrap meat around each egg.
Tie with piece of string or thread.
Place wrapped eggs into saucepan with leftover shoyu mixture and simmer 20 minutes. Cool, slice and serve.

title: crisscross peanut cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda; set aside.

In large bowl, with portable electric mixer at medium speed or wooden spoon, combine butter with remaining ingredients; beat until smooth and fluffy. With wooden spoon, stir in flour mixture until well combined. Refrigerate, covered, at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°. Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Form dough into 1 1/4-inch balls. Place 3 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets.
Flatten with fork, dipped in flour, making a crisscross pattern.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire rack; cool.

title: orange bread
directions: Sift flour before measuring; then resift with baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and add sugar gradually, beating until mixture is fluffy.
Add slightly beaten egg and continue to beat. Add orange juice and rind.
Combine with flour mixture, stirring only enough to moisten the batter.
Do not beat.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix and beat well the sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Then mix and sift flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Mix and add raw apples (chipped), raisins, chopped nuts and coconut.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done at 350°.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Place chicken in a Pyrex dish.
Cover with tortilla chips, thick layers.
Mix soup.
Rinse can out with 1/2 can water; mix with soup.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 can Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add 1 1/2 cups Velveeta cheese.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: cake frosting - white
directions: Place egg whites, Karo syrup, sugar and salt in top half of double boiler.
Beat to mix, then place over boiling water. Continue beating 5 to 7 minutes until stiff peaks.
Remove from fire; add vanilla.
Beat 1 minute more.
Good on chocolate or white cake with 1 package frozen coconut (thawed).

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar.
Add vanilla; remove beaters.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto parchment paper.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes or until dry.

title: mother's turkey dressing
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together and moisten with a mixture of the milk and broth.
Mix until plenty moist but not sloppy.
Can cook in a 13 x 9-inch pan and/or to stuff turkey. Cook at 350° until done (browned around the sides).

title: sweet crisp dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles; discard liquid.
Cut pickles into slices or strips.

Place a layer of the pickles back into the empty jar. Sprinkle layer of the sugar and a few of the cloves over pickles. Continue this method until all ingredients are used, beginning with pickles, sugar and then cloves.

title: old fashioned dumplings
directions: Cut shortening into flour which has been sifted with salt. Add water to flour, beat egg and work into mixture.
Knead lightly and roll on floured board.
Cut into 1-inch squares and drop into boiling chicken broth.

title: o'charley's potato soup
directions: Heat bacon drippings in a large stockpot. Add onion. Saute until tender. Reduce heat to medium. Add flour gradually, stirring constantly until golden brown. Stir in chicken broth and half-and-half.

title: pocinhos de amendoim(south american peanut balls)
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine ground peanuts and milk.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until the mixture forms a ball around the spoon and pulls away from sides of pan, about 5 minutes.
Cool; chill slightly (30 minutes).
Form mixture into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: angel sweets
directions: Melt chips and butter over low heat; remove from heat.
Blend in egg.
Stir in sugar, nuts and marshmallows, blending well. Shape into 1-inch balls or squares.
Roll in coconut.
Chill. Makes about 48.

title: cheddar zucchini bake
directions: Simmer squash to tender; drain.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine egg yolks and sour cream.
Whip egg whites. Place 1/2 of egg mixture, 1/2 of cheese and all of bacon in pan. Repeat layers.
Melt butter; stir in crumbs.
Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no knead "french" bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in a very large bowl. Dissolve sugar and salt in 1 cup warm water.
Add to yeast mixture and mix well.
Add shortening.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir 5 times, 10 minutes apart.

title: onion and potato soup
directions: Saute green and regular onions lightly in butter.
Stir in potatoes, broth and seasonings.
Cover and simmer gently for 45 minutes.
Put in blender and blend to cool.
Stir in milk.
Serve hot or cold in demi cups.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Stew chicken.
Remove meat and cut in chunks.
Return to kettle and add soup, tomatoes, onion, lima beans, potatoes and seasonings.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add corn and butter.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serves 8 or more.

title: spring macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Cool quickly and rinse and drain thoroughly.
Combine macaroni with sour cream, green onion and salt.
Toss lightly.
Chill in refrigerator and serve cold.
Or, if desired, heat in saucepan and serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: graham cracker ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Freeze until like mush.
Take out and whip until light and fluffy.
Put back in freezer until firm. Enjoy!

title: peach crisp
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, oats and cinnamon; cut butter into mixture.
Make it resemble coarse meal.
Stir in pecans.

title: fried okra salad
directions: Just before serving, combine bacon, tomatoes, onions and pepper.
Add okra.
Mix together the oil, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over salad.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Spray shallow 2 qt. casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Add potatoes, ham, and peas; stir gently to mix.
Spoon into sprayed casserole and cover.
Bake covered at 350 for 30 minutes.
Uncover casserole and sprinkle French fried onions over the top.
Bake uncovered for an additional 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and thoroughly heated.

title: low-fat creamy garlic potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes and mash.
Add milk, yogurt, garlic and salt.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until mixture is smooth.
Stir in chives.
Yield: 8 servings (fat 0.1 g per 1/2 cup serving).

title: chewy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat large cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and mushrooms.
Blend cottage cheese, egg and oregano in a small bowl.
Place a thin layer of meat sauce in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add 4 noodles, uncooked, half cheese mixture, half Mozzarella and Parmesan, a little meat sauce and more noodles. Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Cover with plastic wrap and vent.
Cook on High for 15 minutes and Medium for 30 minutes.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Marinate doves for at least 1 hour, covered in Italian dressing.
When ready to grill, wrap each bird with bacon secured with toothpicks.
Grill 10 minutes on each side.

title: fruited cole slaw
directions: Toss shredded cabbage and well-drained fruit cocktail together lightly.
Add cottage cheese; mix and add lemon juice and salt. Chill and serve on bed of lettuce.

title: mulled apple cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove and discard spices; serve hot.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix pudding mix as directed on package.
Drain fruit cocktail and fold into pudding.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: chip cake
directions: Cook pudding as package directs with the 2 cups milk; cool. Stir in box cake mix until all is moist.
Pour in prepared pan. Add 1/2 bag chips, sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Very rich; goes a long way.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook in crock-pot until pepper is transparent, about 15 minutes.

title: oven-barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in a single layer in a buttered shallow baking pan; top with onion slices.
Mix remaining ingredients in a small saucepan; heat to boiling and pour over chicken.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken, skin side up; baste with sauce once or twice.
Cook 30 minutes longer, or until tender and richly glazed.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Makes 3 dozen doughnuts.

title: grilled vegetable sandwich
directions: Preheat the barbecue or stovetop grill.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients
and
put in casserole dish.
Cover and cook for one hour
and
10	minutes at 350°.
Stir halfway through baking.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Form into balls about large walnuts size.
Bake on a cookie sheet 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.
Cool on paper towels.
Spear each ball with a double pointed toothpick to have for finger food.

title: easy-bake chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, lemon juice, instant bouillon and pepper. Place them in a small bowl and stir gently to mix.
Arrange the chicken parts in a single layer in a large baking pan.
Spoon the mixture over each piece of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with Wheatsworth or rye crackers.

title: date bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a medium pan, combine 1/4 cup brown sugar, dates and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon flour into cup, level off.
In a large bowl, combine flour, oats, 1 cup brown sugar, nuts and salt.
Use fork and blend in butter until mixture is coarse crumbs.
Reserve 2 cups of crumb mixture for topping.
Press crumb mixture firmly in bottom of greased pan.
Spread evenly with date mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Pat lightly.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook bacon; add onions and cook.
Add eggs and cook.
Add rice, soy sauce and pepper.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beer wieners
directions: Boil sausages and drain.
Add other ingredients and bring to boil.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: golden shrimp casserole
directions: Arrange alternate layers bread cubes, shrimp and cheese in 1 1/2-quart baking dish or casserole.
Beat eggs with milk; add remaining ingredients.
Pour egg mixture over ingredients in casserole; set casserole in shallow pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: provencal sauteed chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper. Heat oil in heavy Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Working in batches, add chicken and brown on all sides, about 5 minutes per batch.
Transfer chicken to plate.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat from Dutch oven. Add salt pork; saute until golden, about 6 minutes.
Add tomatoes with their juices, broth, wine, thyme, garlic and bay leaves and bring to boil.
Return chicken to oven.
Cover and simmer until chicken is cooked through, about 20 minutes.
Transfer chicken to large bowl. Add olives to Dutch oven and boil until mixture is reduced to 3 cups, about 25 minutes.
Mix in basil.
Return chicken to Dutch oven and stir until heated through, about 3 minutes.
Transfer chicken to shallow serving bowl.
Spoon sauce over and serve!

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix in skillet:
sugar, flour, salt, cocoa, and milk.
Stir constantly on medium/ high heat until the consistency of chocolate pudding.
Will scorch easily.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Wrap bacon around water chestnuts; stick with toothpick.
Bake 1 hour at 250°; drain fat.
Mix brown sugar and catsup.
Heat 45 seconds in microwave.
Spoon over bacon/water chestnuts.
Bake another hour at 250°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: guacamole
directions: Food process all ingredients, chopping onion first on slow to medium speed.
Tabasco sauce can be adjusted to taste.
Cover; refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serve with chips or crudites.

title: saucy skillet dinner
directions: Brown the beef in large skillet, then drain.
Stir in the soup mix, water, tomato sauce, corn and macaroni.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for about 18 minutes or until the macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.

title: curried cashew chicken
directions: Heat butter in a large skillet; gently fry garlic, onions and ginger until soft and golden, stirring occasionally.
Add curry powder and chili and stir for about a minute.
Add salt, tomatoes and cilantro and cook to a pulp, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Add chicken.
Stir well to coat chicken with spice mixture.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add Garam Masala and yogurt and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in ground cashews (use coffee grinder, blender or food processor to grind) and heat through.
Sprinkle extra chopped cilantro on top for color.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: barbecued chicken in brown paper bag
directions: Grease inside of heavy brown paper bag.
Combine first 12 ingredients.
Dip chicken in sauce.
Place in bag.
Pour any remaining sauce over chicken.
Fold end of bag in double fold. Place bag in roaster.
Bake for 15 minutes at 500°.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open bag until cooking time is completed.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour, cinnamon and nutmeg and combine to mixture.
Add vanilla, apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into
a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse pronto
directions: In blender, combine water, coffee and chocolate chips.
Cover and blend until smooth, about 1 minute.
Add sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend each egg in before adding the next. Pour into serving dishes.
Refrigerate until served.
Serve with whipped cream and chocolate curls, if desired.

title: cool whip fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk; refrigerate for one hour. Add rest of ingredients, mix well and refrigerate.
Makes a big bowl.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together. Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: creamy texas dip
directions: Drain picante sauce, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.

title: blondies
directions: Grease 15 x 10-inch pan.
Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add four, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread in pan and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan before cutting.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Mix and form into balls. Brown and set aside.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cook broccoli as directed on box.
Put cooked broccoli on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Break chicken up into bite sizes and put on top of broccoli.
In another bowl, mix Miracle Whip, soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour mixture over chicken and distribute evenly.
Shred cheese and cover mixture.
Add bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: kraut salad
directions: Rinse kraut in cold water.
Chop celery, onions and pepper. Mix all well.
Will keep in refrigerator up to 1 week.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms(appetizer)
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Cut cream cheese into cubes.
Mix with warm sausage.
Stuff mushroom caps full (won't run over). Bake at 325° about 20 minutes.
There will be moisture in the pan so use jelly roll pan to bake.
Serve immediately.
These are always gone before the party ends!

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix ingredients.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let set for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cut through with sharp knife.
Makes approximately 60 pieces.
Can also freeze and reheat.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Pour 3/4 cup of salt over cucumbers.
Cover with ice and mix well.
Set for 3 hours.
Place something heavy over top so cucumbers will lower into cold ice and water as it melts.
Drain and wash cucumbers.
Mix sugar, vinegar, etc., and bring almost to boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: diabetic blueberry muffins
directions: Lightly coat the blueberries with the 2 teaspoons flour (you can shake the flour and berries together in paper bag).
In a large bowl, mix together 1 3/4 cups flour, baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In a small bowl, beat the eggs or egg substitute lightly.
Add oil, orange juice and grated rind.
Add the liquid to dry mixture; stir a few times gently.
Before the 2 mixtures are fully combined, add berries and lemon rind.
Spoon into muffin cups coated with nonstick vegetable spray, filling each cup about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion, tomatoes and eggs; set aside.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; mix until smooth.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Cook until done.
Add oleo while chicken is boiling.
Remove chicken; let cool.
Tear into small pieces.
Cook spaghetti or noodles in broth.
Cook until broth is just about gone.
Add chicken, Ro-Tel and 1 to 1 1/2 pounds of cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put into casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream the Wesson oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Sift flour with soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Pour in buttermilk and mix well. Add the cut up prunes and chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Let bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: betty's chocolate pie
directions: Mix cream and sugar in a heavy pan.
In blender, mix milk, Quik, flour, salt and egg yolks.
Blend.
Add to pan and bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 minutes. Add oleo and vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped egg whites, sweetened with 6 tablespoons sugar. Brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, white sugar, vanilla, eggs, 1/2 cup butter and milk until smooth.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Crumble together flour, 1/2 cup butter, brown sugar and pecans; sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion, pepper and seasonings in butter in large pot. Stir in soup, milk, cream cheese and corn.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Cover; reduce heat to low.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes. Makes 16 servings.
Works well to halve the recipe.
May add fresh shrimp if desired.
Excellent soup!

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Combine the flour with the drained pineapple juice, also sugar, salt and egg. Bring to a boil.
After mixture has thickened, add cubed cheese and combine with marshmallows and stir into juice mixture.
Add nuts and pineapple bits.

title: nana's homemade chicken soup
directions: Add chicken to 12-quart pot filled with water.
Boil chicken for 2 minutes.
Lower heat to simmer and skim off foam from chicken.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer several hours until broth becomes dark and vegetables are tender.
Drain broth from chicken and vegetables.
Carrots and chicken can be cut into small pieces and put back in broth.
To remove fat from broth, refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Skim off fat from top.
When ready to serve, cook noodles and add to broth or make Tortellini Escarole (recipe follows).

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients and stir well.
Make 1-inch balls.
Press crisscross with a fork. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chess pie(serving size:  8.  preparation time:  1:00)
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugars and melted butter.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla, flour and salt.
Stir in cream and mix well.
Line pie pan with pastry, crimping edges decoratively.
Pour filling into pie shell. Bake at 400° for ten minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°. Bake 25 to 30 minutes longer, until filling is set.

title: tomato refresher
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Chill.
Stir before serving. Float paper thin lemon slices atop.
Makes 5 (4 ounce) servings.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Layer vegetables in glass bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Pour dressing over and let set until ready to serve.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
Set aside.
Mix together pudding and milk.
Add whipped topping to pudding.
Add this mixture to cream cheese mixture.
Layer with crushed cookies and add gummy worms.
Serve after chilling 2 hours.

title: holiday stripe cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.

title: spinach-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops from tomatoes.
Large tomatoes can be halved.
Remove pulp, leaving shells intact.
Sprinkle inside with salt and pepper.

title: blueberry loaf
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat margarine and sugar in bowl until light and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until fluffy.
Add flour and milk.
Beat well.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle mixture of sugar,
cinnamon and nutmeg on top before baking.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In large saucepan, pour oil.
Add cut up onions and brown chicken in onions and oil for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Add both cans of tomatoes along with a 1/2 can of water to each.
Add whole can of peas.
Add salt and pepper to taste, approximately 1 tablespoon of garlic powder and 2 or 3 dashes of oregano.
Cook for approximately 1 hour.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Heat all to a boil. Stir.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Stir together melted butter and sugar.
Resift flour with salt and cinnamon and nutmeg and add butter and sugar mixture.
Add persimmon pulp, soda dissolved in warm water, brandy and vanilla. Add eggs, mixing thoroughly, but lightly.
Add raisins and nuts, stirring until mixed.
Put in buttered, steam-type, covered mold and steam for 2 1/2 hours or until firm.
Spoon Brandy Whipped Cream Sauce over pudding.
Recipe is elsewhere.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix together and bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Soak wild rice overnight.
Mix all together.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Add more water if needed.
Top with slivered almonds.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together the shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Sift the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt and stir in. Chill dough several hours.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll balls in a mixture of the 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400° until lightly browned but still soft.
(They will puff up and then flatten with crinkled top.)

title: monster toast
directions: Pour milk into 4 different cups.
Color the milk with food colorings.
Using a clean paintbrush, paint a piece of white bread.
Toast the bread lightly in the toaster.
Kids like to make this!

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in bowl as listed.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Toss before serving.

title: russian cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Dice apples.
Grate carrots.
Slice onion. Combine and moisten with mayonnaise.
Add sugar and sour cream. Mix thoroughly.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening and mix well.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Work together until all flour is moistened.
Refrigerate.
When ready to use, take out as much dough as needed.
Roll out dough.
Cut as you would biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Dough keeps several days.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Add water, margarine and vanilla.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Put peaches on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spicy molasses baked apples
directions: Combine molasses, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon, nutmeg and 1/3 cup water.
Core apples, peel 1/3 way down.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Simmer onion in melted oleo. Combine all ingredients in buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: icebox pecan cookies
directions: Mix shortening,
sugar	and
egg.
Add	flour, soda and salt. Add vanilla.
Mix
well.
Shape
into rolls and wrap in waxed paper or
foil
and store in refrigerator until ready to bake at 350°
until
lightly browned.
These may be frozen and thawed slightly and sliced and baked.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and cocoa thoroughly.
Add, but do not mix, butter, placed in middle of dish, and evaporated milk.
Put in microwave on High and cook 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Put in buttered dish and refrigerate.

title: cranberry pancake syrup
directions: Add
all
ingredients, except the Karo syrup.
Low boil for 10
minutes
and
simmer until it thickens.
Keep a small dish in the
freezer
and test a little in the dish until the thickness is what you want.
Then add the Karo syrup and mix. Put
in jars and cool.
This will keep in the refrigerator for quite
a
few weeks. It if changes texture, place in a pan of hot water.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Gradually add to the cream cheese, blending until smooth.
Add fruit juice. Chill until thoroughly thickened.
Add the fruit cocktail and fold in the Dream Whip.
Set.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients and toss together very lightly as not to break orange sections.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Combine melted chocolate and butter in large bowl and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients for filling.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix margarine and crushed vanilla wafers.
Spread evenly in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread coconut evenly over vanilla wafer mixture. Spread chocolate chips evenly over coconut.
Spread the chopped nuts over chocolate chips. Pour the Eagle Brand milk over entire. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Boil zucchini 5 minutes or microwave without water for 4 minutes. Drain if boiled.
In a separate bowl, combine sour cream and chicken soup (no water).
Add zucchini, onion, carrots and fold together into sour cream and soup.
In a separate bowl, combine stuffing mix with seasoning and melted butter.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, alternate layers of zucchini and stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: nonfat chocolate milk
directions: Mix together.
Add 2 teaspoons with boiling water for cocoa. May add a pinch of cinnamon per cup.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bowl, add all ingredients and mix until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty bowl into shallow baking pan and bake approximately 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish with parsley and serve. Serves 8.

title: marble cake
directions: Cream butter well.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add vanilla; beat until very fluffy.
Add rum.
Beat again.
Slowly add flour and milk, alternately, a little at a time until all used up.
Beat egg whites until very fluffy and fold into other mixture.
Put 2/3 of mixture into greased baking pan (Bundt).
To the remaining 1/3 of mixture, add the cocoa mixture and put it on top of the other mixture in the baking pan.
With a fork or spoon, make marble design.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: delicious vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: nigerian peanut soup
directions: Chop and saute onion and celery in 4 tablespoons oil.
Add 1 tablespoon flour then 1 cup stock and blend well.
Bring to boil, then puree.
Blend 1 cup stock, 2 cups milk and 1 cup peanut butter.
Heat gently.
Don't boil.
Serve hot or cold.

title: polynesian pork
directions: Cook pork in butter until brown; drain off fat.
Drain juice from pineapple tidbits; reserve fruit.
Combine juice with next 4 ingredients.
Stir in water which has been mixed with cornstarch. Pour over meat.
Cook, stirring until sauce is thickened.
Cover. Simmer 30 minutes.
Add onion and pineapple tidbits.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin raisin cake
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture and beat 1 minute on medium (on electric mixer).
Stir in pineapple, raisins, pecans and vanilla.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with waxed paper.
Grease waxed paper.
Spoon batter into pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
(Toothpick should come out clean when inserted in middle.) Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove and peel off paper.
Cool completely and frost.
Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onion and garlic fine; brown in 3 tablespoons olive oil in frypan until soft.
Add 1 can tomato juice, tomato paste (rinse can) and tomato sauce.
Add fresh parsley and pinch of soda; stir. Add salt to taste.
Cover and simmer.
Fry sausage or brown hamburger; drain.
Cut sausage up; add to sauce after it has simmered 1 hour.
Add basil, oregano and stir.
Cook 2 to 3 hours, cooking uncovered the last hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cook in water until tender.
Mash them right in the pot.
Add remaining ingredients and more water to desired consistency.
Cook on low for about 20 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: bean salad
directions: Chill the 2 cans of red kidney beans.
Strain and rinse. Combine beans with diced celery, onion and pickle relish.
Moisten with salad dressing to which a drop of vinegar has been added.

title: pumpkin bread(2 loaves)
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients. Mix at medium speed for 1 minute. Add the rest of ingredients.
Mix on low until moistened. Mix at medium for 1 minute.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts. Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 40 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes; cut into squares.
Invert each square onto dessert dish. Top with ice cream and spoon sauce over each serving.
Makes 9 servings.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg white.
Roll in nuts.
Place a about 1 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 5 minutes in 375° oven.
Remove from oven, quickly press thumb gently on top of each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 8 minutes longer.
Cool. Place in thumbprints, a bit of candied fruit, sparkling jelly or tinted confectioners sugar icing.

title: sugar biscuits
directions: Add sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Drop biscuits in deep fryer until brown on both sides, then roll them in sugar mixture.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: In a large Baggie, mix a dash of salt, pepper and paprika to a good amount of Bisquick.
Wet chicken with water or milk and shake well in Baggie (no more than 2 pieces at a time).
Once chicken is well coated, place in 9 x 13-inch pan with a little oil and roll chicken.
Bake at 350° until chicken is brown and crisp.
You may want to turn chicken once during cooking.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix with dressing and serve.

title: quick golden stew
directions: Cook carrots, potatoes and onions 10 minutes.
Add peas and frankfurters and cook 5 minutes more.
Stir in celery soup and cheese spread.

title: easy 4-layer chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package. Pour into two round cake pan, and bake as directed on package.

title: chicken with sour cream sauce
directions: Bake chicken with 4 cups water, onion and bouillon cubes at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Season if desired with salt, pepper and garlic powder).
Take chicken out of drippings and set aside; add pint of sour cream to drippings and mix well.
Return chicken to sour cream mixture; bake at 200° for 30 minutes and serve. Garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: salad croutons(child's recipe)
directions: In bowl, combine oil, oregano, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle over bread cubes and toss until coated.
Spread on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
