Bake at 275° until crisp.
Cool and serve with fresh tossed salad.

title: no flour peanut cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use teaspoon at a time to drop onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Let cool before taking out of pan.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine butter, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and salt. In a plastic bag, combine crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Dip chicken in butter mixture, then shake in crumb mixture. Place in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Drizzle with any remaining butter mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and juices are clear.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix pudding and milk together until thick.
Add Cool Whip and Amaretto.
Serve with favorite fruits.
Bananas are great!

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add the blueberries.
Combine the well-beaten egg, milk and oil.
Stir them together.
Spoon the mixture into a greased muffin pan.
Fill each cup 3/4 full.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes at 425° until the tops are golden brown.
Makes 12 large or 18 medium size muffins.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with spoon (mixture will be thick). Spread in well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients by hand and put over cake mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not open oven door while baking.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Form into whatever you like!
Can be eaten too!

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Pare watermelon rind, removing green and pink portions.
Cut rind into 1-inch pieces.
Dissolve salt in water; add rind and let stand 6 hours or overnight.
Drain; rinse and cover with cold water in large saucepan.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag.
Add spices and remaining ingredients to saucepan.

title: dandelion salad
directions: Combine dandelion leaves, mushrooms, tomatoes, croutons and almonds.
Toss with Italian dressing and sprinkle with cheese.

title: chocolate walnut bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, syrup and vanilla, using a hand mixer. Add bread and nuts.
Place pudding in a casserole dish placed in a large pan containing hot water.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: bitsy bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut each biscuit into three pieces. Roll each piece into a small ball.
Dip balls in honey.
Roll in coconut.
Place 3 balls in each muffin cup in muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a big pot.
Stir thoroughly; bring to a boil.
Lower heat to medium and cook for 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve with saltines, corn chips or cornbread.

title: southern okra
directions: Combine first
3 ingredients and set aside in a covered saucepan.
Cook
okra in boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and	set
aside.
Put
oil
in a skillet and on medium heat.
Saute
onions
and pepper until tender.
Stir in sugar mixture
and	tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Add okra and simmer until
heated
through, stirring as little as possible. Serve with rice.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: cheese snack
directions: Pour dressing over sliced apples, carrots and cheese. Microwave 1 minute.

title: veggie soup
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: my favorite meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Shape mixture and place in loaf pan (22 x 11 x 6 cm) or divide mixture and place in muffin pans.
Bake for 50 minutes in loaf pan or 30 minutes in muffin pans.
Remove from oven and garnish with catsup and parsley sprigs.

title: six-week muffins
directions: This
make a good breakfast or dinner accompaniment for unexpected guests.

title: honey cake
directions: Dissolve instant coffee in water.
Combine with honey, water and oil.
Blend all dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Beat eggs until light; add sugar gradually.
Add flour mixture and coffee, honey and oil and stir in walnuts.
Pour into a greased and wax paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325 ° for 50 minutes.
Remove from pan to wire rack.
Better after a few days.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Remove any spikes or tough leaves from artichoke hearts. Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into a 9-inch square baking pan and sprinkle some paprika over top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot with assorted crackers.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Drain pineapple chunks and save juice.
If necessary, add water to make one cup of liquid.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and cook until to forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Beat until mixture is creamy.
Pour into buttered thin pans.

title: corn bread
directions: Break bread in small pieces.
Add salt, sugar, egg and water. Beat until well blended.
Add meal and baking powder; mix well. Add milk to make a thin batter.
Melt butter in an 8 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour batter in hot margarine.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: "best cheesecake you ever tasted"
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease a spring pan (do not flour).

title: shrimp ring
directions: Melt cream cheese and soup.
Remove from stove and add dissolved gelatine, chopped celery, chopped onion, shrimp and mayo.
Pour into mold.
May be used as a dip.
I use a ring mold and fill the center with black olives and garnish.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Separate rolls.
Combine chicken and cheese.
Reserve about 1/2 the mixture for use in sauce.
Place about 3 tablespoons of remaining chicken-cheese mixture on each crescent and roll up. Place roll-ups seam side down in a lightly greased 7 1/2 x 11 3/4-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and milk together.
Add reserved chicken and cheese mixture.
Add pimento, if desired.
Pour over roll-ups and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch slush
directions: Boil sugar in water until dissolved.
Cool and add the next 4 ingredients.
Mix well and freeze in 2 containers.
Thaw 2 hours before using.
In punch bowl, pour 7-Up and lemon juice over frozen mixture to serve.

title: noodle bars
directions: In a small cookie sheet, layer the ingredients in order listed.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool, then cut.

title: caramels
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add corn syrup and sugar. Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add 1 1/2 cans of sweetened condensed milk.
Mix flour thoroughly with remaining milk; then add to corn syrup-sugar mixture.
Boil until mixture darkens and forms a medium-hard ball (240°).
Stir constantly or mixture will stick.
Add vanilla and pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch pieces with sharp, buttered knife.
Wrap squares in waxed paper.

title: flyin' a chili, keen burrito
directions: Brown and crumble 3 pounds hamburger in a large skillet.
Add 30 skinned green chilies, seeds and all.
Add 2 cans tomatoes diced with chili.
Simmer and serve as beanless chili.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil the margarine, 1 cup water and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Remove from heat and add flour, salt and 2 cups sugar. Beat in baking soda, eggs and sour cream.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 365° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs. Beat well. Add flour, cinnamon, flavoring, carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done in tube pan, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: my created cube steak
directions: In large skillet, quickly brown steaks on both sides in hot vegetable oil.
Add onion; cook until onion is almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Combine water and mushroom gravy mix and pour over steaks and onion mixture.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes. Skim off any excess fat.
Serve with gravy.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Cut rhubarb in small pieces and place in bottom of oblong cake pan.
Mix jello and sugar.
Pour 1 cup water in corner of pan. Mix cake mix and butter.
Sprinkle over top of rhubarb.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add the egg yolks, reserving the whites.
Add the melted unsweetened chocolate.
Add the milk and the flour mixture alternately.
Stir in stiffly beaten egg whites by hand.
Bake in 2 (8 x 8-inch) round pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan at 350° until done.

title: cranberry glazed chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix cranberry sauce, 1/4 cup orange juice and 2 tablespoons margarine in saucepan.
Heat until smooth.
Place chicken, skin side up, in shallow 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brush with half of the glaze and bake 40 minutes.

title: bacon-chestnut tidbits
directions: You will need some toothpicks.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Mix everything together.
Put some of the mix into a cookie decorator.
Punch cookies out onto a cookie sheet.
Decorate the cookies with any kind of sprinkles.
Place in oven for 10 minutes at 325°.
Enjoy!

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Place frozen ice cream in a punch bowl; pour mixture of eggnog and milk over ice cream; stir a little.
When serving a cup, add Cool Whip and a dash of nutmeg.
Eggnog will be thick like a milk shake.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cut the cheese up into cubes and mix with 1 cup of Ro-Tel. Put in microwave until cheese is melted. Then mix in 1 cup of cream of chicken soup. Put chicken and spaghetti noodles into a casserole dish. Then pour the cheese, Ro-Tel and cream of chicken over the noodles and chicken. Put in the oven for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana oatmeal bread
directions: Grease
two
x
x
3-inch
loaf
pans; set aside. Preheat
oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl combine bananas, oats and milk;
set aside.
In a large bowl cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each
addition.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately
with banana
mixture
to creamed mixture.
Spoon into prepared
pans. Bake
1 hour.
Remove from pans and cool on a wire
rack.
Wrap well
and
freeze
up to 3 months.
Makes 2 loaves.
Each
loaf makes
18 1/2-inch slices, about 180 calories each.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar, syrup and butter.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 375° until set.

title: herb pastry for quiche
directions: In a large bowl, mix together flour, parsley flakes, dill, dry mustard and salt.
Add butter and mix until ingredients resemble coarse meal.
Sprinkle with cold water 1 tablespoon at a time until mixture is moist enough to leave sides of bowl.
Shape into ball and roll out for pie plate.
Prick bottom of crust and brush with egg.
Cook 10 minutes.
Fill with quiche and cook until done in a 400° oven.

title: bacon rolls
directions: Trim the edges of the bread and cut into strips of three per slice.
Combine cheese, onion and green pepper.
Spread cheese mixture on bread and roll, then roll half a slice of bacon around each.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Drain on paper towels. This freezes well.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend together with pastry cutter.
Add one egg mixed with 1 tablespoon vinegar with enough water to have 1 cup of liquid. Makes 6 crusts.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or Tupperware container.
Slice ice cream and arrange on Oreo cookies.
Melt hot fudge topping and pour over ice cream.
Cut up nuts and arrange on top.
Put in freezer to set up about 1/2 hour. Spread Cool Whip on and set back in freezer.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour
and salt.
Add broth and milk, all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce is thick.
Add chicken, drained mushrooms and pimiento. Heat until bubbly.
Serve over toast or rice.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix Hidden Valley and oil together.
Stack 3 brown paper bags one inside the other.
Put in all snack items.
Add oil mix. Either tie or staple bags shut.
Shake 15 minutes.
Let stand overnight.
(Freezes well.)

title: diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Combine egg, pumpkin, sweetener, salt and spices. Add milk and blend. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Grease casserole dish with butter; add eggs and beat.
Add pineapple, sugar and tapioca.
Mix well.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Set casserole dish in a pan of water.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla. Beat in eggs one at a time. Blend in coca or chocolate, stir in flour and nuts. Bake in 8 x 8 greased pan at 325 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in 1/2.
Remove yolks and press through sieve. Combine yolks with remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
If desired, add more seasoning and salad dressing.
Refill whites with fork, spoon or pastry tube.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Melt butter or oleo and mix with crushed crackers. Cook frozen vegetables according to package directions and drain. After vegetables cool, combine all ingredients (except cracker mixture) in a 2-quart or 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top casserole with cracker mixture. Bake at 350° to 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the cream cheese and oleo; stir in vanilla.
Add powdered sugar, a little at a time, until smooth.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together muffin mix and pudding mix.
Add eggs and milk; stir to blend.
Batter will be lumpy.
Coat an 8-inch square pan with vegetable cooking spray and spread batter in pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: ham & cheese appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread into 9x13x2-inch greased pan.

title: dried beans and sausage
directions: Pick over beans and wash well.
Put in a large pot with the water and let it come to a boil.
Turn off heat and let stand about one hour.
Return to boil, then reduce heat and let simmer until beans are tender, adding more water as necessary.
In a large skillet, brown sausage and onions, breaking up the sausage as it cooks.
Drain fat.
Stir sausage and onions into the beans and let simmer until beans are very tender.
Add salt to taste.

title: naples breadsticks
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 cup oil and 1 cup of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Shape dough into roll, 10 inches long.
Cut into 36 equal parts.
Roll each part into rope, 8 inches long for thick breadsticks, 10 inches long for thin breadsticks.
Place about 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet. Brush with oil.
Cover; let rise in warm place about 20 minutes. Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg white and 1 tablespoon water slightly; brush over breadsticks and sprinkle with coarse salt. Bake until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen breadsticks.

title: oysters in a cloud
directions: Beat egg whites and tartar until stiff peaks form.

Shuck oysters. Boil in their juices and seafood seasoning until edges curl. Drop egg whites by spoonful onto a greased baking pan. Be creative with shapes; make an indentation in each egg white. Broil until golden brown.
Place 1 oyster in each egg white and serve garnished with a dash of cocktail sauce or a drop of lime juice.

title: pink popcorn
directions: Place the freshly popped popcorn in a very large buttered bowl.
Set aside while making the white sugar syrup.

title: party potatoes
directions: Make potatoes for 12 as instructed on box.
Beat potatoes, cream cheese and sour cream.
Place in casserole dish.
Brush with melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian dressing chicken and potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes and chicken in a baking pan or dish.
Cover with the Italian dressing.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: spicy whip prune cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream together shortening, milk and prune juice.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients gradually.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until done.
Test with toothpick.
Can be baked in layer or tube pan.

title: souper chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine soups, milk and rice in prepared pan. Lay chicken pieces on top. Sprinkle with onion soup mix and black pepper. Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick and easy dump punch
directions: Pour juices and ice or ice ring into large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: apple crisp #1
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place apples in greased pan or a baking dish (1 1/2-quart).
Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: crab and shrimp bisque
directions: Make a small roux on side to add in later.
Saute onion, bell pepper, celery, onion tops and parsley for about 15 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup water.
Pour in with sauteed mixture and cook for about 10 minutes.
Add in soups and 2 cans of water. Cook on low heat, stirring constantly, for 20 minutes.
Add desired crab and shrimp and cook for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: bird nests(candy)
directions: Melt chocolate until smooth.
Mix in a few pretzels at a time. Fish out and drop by spoonful on wax paper or cupcake papers. Have the appearance of a bird nest.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine butter or oleo, salt and water in saucepan.
Heat to boiling; add flour to boiling mixture.
Beat vigorously until mixture leaves sides of pan and does not cling to spoon.
Remove from fire and cool slightly.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition, until mixture is smooth. Drop by tablespoonfuls in well oiled muffin tins.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Lower heat to 350°.
Continue baking for 10 minutes or until firm and dry.
Remove from oven; cool. Cut a slit in the side of each with a sharp knife.
Using a spoon or pastry tube, insert cream filling.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or cover with chocolate sauce.

title: rice cheddar
directions: Saute onions in margarine until golden brown.
Add pimentos and rice; cook over low heat until thoroughly heated, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese.

title: chili-cheese cornsticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease cornstick pan well.
In medium bowl combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Add egg, milk and oil.
With wire whisk beat just until smooth (1 minute).
Stir in cheese and chilies.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Gel in refrigerator until set.
Mix crushed pineapple, juice and pecans.
Pour over Jell-O mixture (after it's set).
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over pineapple and nut mixture.
Refrigerate.
Very good.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chopped chicken in a cake pan.
Pour cream of chicken soup over chicken.

title: bertha's friday special
directions: In 1-quart casserole, blend soup and milk.
Stir in tuna, eggs and peas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with chips and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: candied pecans
directions: Toast pecan halves at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Mix cinnamon, salt and sugar. Beat egg whites. Blend egg whites and dry ingredients. Pour pecans into mixture. Melt butter in cookie sheet. Pour pecan mixture into melted butter. Spread evenly. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn at least every 10 minutes.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Pat fish dry with paper towels.
Cut fish into serving size pieces.
In deep fryer or heavy saucepan, heat 2 to 3 inches oil to 375°.
In shallow dish, combine pancake mix, lemon pepper, beer and egg; mix until smooth.
Place crumbs in another shallow dish.
Dip fish into batter then into crumbs, covering completely.
Fry in hot oil for 3 to 4 minutes, turning once, until golden brown and fish flakes with fork.
Keep fish warm until all pieces are cooked. Serve with lemon wedges or tartar sauce, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine
ingredients in large mixing bowl;
stir
until
all dry ingredients are moistened. Bake
in greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper in oleo.
Add tomato soup, tomato sauce, corn, chili powder, mustard, salt, pepper, mushrooms and cooked noodles.
Place in casserole dish and place grated cheese on top.
Pour milk over the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil 5 minutes together the following:
2 cups water and sugar. Let cool, then mix other ingredients.
Add syrup and let stand overnight, if possible.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 325°. Makes 2 loaves of bread.

title: energy bars
directions: Spread oats in a shallow pan.
Toast in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown, stirring once.

title: punch
directions: Make syrup by boiling sugar and 6 cups water for 10 minutes. Cool and add juice.
Before serving, add ginger ale.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in 2 1/2 cups cold water; set aside. In a saucepan, place 2 cups cold water, jello and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat; add gelatine mixture and mix well. Add 1 cup water to this.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spray pan with Pam or butter.
Cut in squares.

title: coconut snowballs
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Hold cupcakes, top-side down, in palm of hand; spread mixture on bottom and sides.
Press coconut onto frosting.
Place cupcakes, top-side down, on serving platter. Drizzle with melted chocolate, if desired.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Spoon batter into muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one hour yeast rolls
directions: Warm milk.
Add salt, oil and sugar.
Mix yeast with flour and pour milk mixture over it.
Mix well.
Knead a few times and roll out on a floured surface.
Cut out rolls or pat them out like biscuits.
Brush the tops with butter; let rise in a warm place for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: green congealed salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together in a bowl.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Cover and chill. Serve.

title: tennessee pumpkin bread
directions: Grease a loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Stir in pumpkin and then stir in dry ingredients in 4 additions, alternately with water until just smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: sourdough starter and bread
directions: Day One:
In a medium bowl, combine 2 cups of the flour with yeast.
Stir.
Stir in the water until mixture is blended.
Cover the bowl with a clean towel and allow the mixture to sit at room temperature 24 hours.

title: frosted spice cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add molasses, egg and milk; mix well.
Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in walnuts, raisins and dates.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: weeknight chili
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, cook ground meat 4 to 5 minutes or until no longer pink, stirring frequently. Drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. If desired, top with chopped onion, shredded cheese or sour cream. Makes 4 servings.

title: wisconsin cheese fudge
directions: Melt together the cheese and butter.
Sift together the sugar and cocoa.
Add to cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nonfat dry milk, vanilla and nuts.
Pat into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Chill.
Makes 3 pounds.
(Recipe can be doubled.)

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Break sausage up and fry; drain on paper towel.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread croutons evenly over bottom. Sprinkle cheese over croutons and sausage over cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and dry mustard; pour over sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit delight
directions: Cream together the sugar, sour cream and butter.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Spread mixture in pie crust; cool for 30 minutes.
Whip the cream, sour cream and powdered sugar; mix well.
Add pineapple, pecans, cherries and coconut.
Spread mix over chilled filling.
Chill pie until ready to serve.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well.
Store mix in an airtight container.

title: lo-cal heavenly hash
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Put everything in blender except Grape-Nuts.
Pour in dish, let cool, then sprinkle Grape-Nuts on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick and easy pound cake
directions: In electric mixer, beat butter and eggs.
Add sugar, flour and flavorings.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pans. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
(Fill pans only half full.)
Serve with fresh strawberries.

title: sherry trifle
directions: Spread ladyfingers with raspberry jam; arrange in a glass dish.
Moisten the sponge with sherry.
Make Jell-O, using 1/2 cup less water.
Pour over ladyfingers, then add drained fruit.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Make custard or vanilla pudding; let cool.
When cold, pour on top of Jell-O.
Whip heavy cream and spoon on top of custard.
Decorate with cherries and almonds.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal, boiling water and margarine and let stand 20 minutes.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add to oatmeal mixture and mix well.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Add sugar and dry jello.
Remove from heat.
Add applesauce and pineapple.
Pour into dish or mold.

title: bean bake
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
Brown onion rings in bacon fat.
Add brown sugar, salt, dry mustard, garlic salt and cider vinegar.
Cook in skillet for 20 minutes uncovered. Drain lima, butter and kidney beans; put in casserole.
Add baked beans undrained.
Mix.
Pour cooked mixture over the top. Sprinkle bacon on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crab canoe
directions: Hollow out French bread loaf.
Cut hollowed out bread in chunks.
Combine mayo, Colby cheese, green onions and crab meat. Put mixture in hollowed out bread loaf.
Bake at 325 for 30 minutes until bubbly.
The last 10 minutes add a little more of the grated cheese on top.
Place bread cubes around loaf and use to dip with.

title: simply tomatoes(low-fat)
directions: Core the tomatoes and cut them crosswise in to thick slices. Divide among individual plates.
Sprinkle with the basil garlic and pepper.
Drizzle with the oil.

title: spinach in bread bed
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread.
Cut circle and hollow out 1 loaf of bread.
Put filling inside.
Cut remaining loaf into cubes.
Place cubes around bread and spinach bed.
Serve with knife to spread over the the cubes.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar. Work in vanilla, flour and nuts. Shape into balls the size of walnuts. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool; roll in powdered sugar. Yield: 5 dozen.

title: cheese bread
directions: Roll one package of crescent rolls in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pinch seams together.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Spread creamed mixture on top of rolls. Roll second package of crescent rolls on top of cheese layer. Pinch seams.
Beat egg white (not stiff) and brush on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar, egg yolks and oil.
Stir soda into buttermilk.
Add flour to batter, alternating with buttermilk. Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold them into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's gelatin fruit salad
directions: Make dressing a day ahead.
Combine pineapple juice, sugar, egg, cornstarch and butter in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and flavorings.
Mix in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Roll out and cut into shapes.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil; cool. Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill overnight in mold. Serves 24.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain.
Stir remaining ingredients in with warm carrots until coated.
Salt to taste. Yields 6 servings. Preparation time:
5 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk until all is added.
Add vanilla.
Line bottom of tube pan with wax paper and spray pan with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: soy cottage cheese
directions: Make soy grits from raw or toasted soy beans, ground to grits in blender.
Stir ingredients together.
Cook in double boiler, without stirring, for 3 hours.
Cool.
Remove a portion and gently mix curds with enough lemon juice to make sour.
Shape into mound. Garnish and serve as cottage cheese.

title: shrimp noodle soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in large saucepan. Break up chicken-flavor Ramen noodle soup mix (reserve seasoning packets). Add noodles to water with all remaining ingredients except shrimp. Cook 5 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in shrimp and seasoning packets. Cook an additional 2 or 3 minutes or until shrimp are thoroughly heated.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook peppers 7 to 10 minutes in boiling salted water.
Sprinkle salt in skillet; brown ground beef.
Add garlic and tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add chili powder, pepper, onion and rice.
Fill peppers; top with cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°. Freezes beautifully.

title: flounder thermidor
directions: Roll up fish fillets.
Arrange in baking dish.
Pour milk over; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chiso no agemono
directions: Combine all ingredients except chiso to make batter.
Dip leaves or seeds in batter and deep fry.

title: peach gelatin salad
directions: Drain peaches.
Add water to peach juice to make 1 cup.
Add to juice, vinegar, cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Boil for 2 minutes. Let stand.
Make Jell-O as usual, only 1 cup water though.
Combine with boiled mixture.
Arrange sliced peaches in Pyrex dish.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Chill until solid.
Serve on lettuce. Mayonnaise may be spread on top.

title: mystical ice cream pie
directions: Stir cookies into softened ice cream; spread in prepared crust.
Freeze two to three hours or until firm.
Let stand five to ten minutes before cutting into wedges to serve.
Makes eight servings.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Separate and unroll bread sticks.
Place 3 pepperoni slices in single layer over half of each bread stick.
Fold remaining half over top; seal end and twist.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Combine next 3 ingredients; sprinkle over sticks.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well.
In a small bowl, make a paste with cocoa and red food coloring.
Add this to the mixture.
Mix well.
Mix salt, vanilla and milk.
Add flour a little at a time alternately with the milk mixture; mix well.
Mix vinegar and baking soda in a small bowl, then add this to cake mixture.
Mix well; do not beat.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour in greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Moisten avocado with juice to prevent browning.
Add water to remaining juice to make 1/2 cup.
Saute celery, onion and shrimp in margarine for 3 minutes. Add curry.
Cook 1 minute.
Blend in soup and remaining juice. Stir in pineapple.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot cooked rice. Garnish with avocado slices.

title: bark candy
directions: If candy coating is in a solid piece, break into squares. Place in a single layer in a 2 quart casserole.
Microwave at Medium for 4 to 7 minutes, or until coating can be stirred smooth, stirring once or twice.
Add nuts, seed or raisins.
Stir to coat evenly.
Spread on wax paper to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cool until set, then break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla and beat well. Add dry ingredients. Roll into balls, dip in sugar and flatten with a fork dipped in flour. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for 10-12 minutes.

title: neiman marcus bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and 1 stick butter and spread into greased 9
x
13-inch
pan.
Mix
and
pour over dough 1 stick butter,
powdered
sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool and cut after 24 hours.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in glass bowl or stainless steel bowl.
Chill.

title: potato bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash, scrub and dice into 1-inch cubes. (Do not peel.)
Place margarine in large pan.
Melt in oven.
Add potato cubes.
Stir and spoon butter over.
Sprinkle generously with seasonings as listed in order.
Bake 30 minutes.
Stir and bake another 10 to 15 minutes until fork-tender.
Twenty pounds of potatoes serve 75 to 80 people.

title: vegetable dipper
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, seasonings and carrots.
Blend well.
Serve chilled with your favorite fresh vegetables.

title: "wop" bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; mix mayonnaise and margarine and add to mixture.
Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Spread mixture on bread halves.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning on top.
Bake at 350° until melted.
Do not wrap in foil.
Great party treat.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add dry ingredients and milk. Beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan.
Drain juice from peaches.
Lay peaches on batter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and then sprinkle with cinnamon as desired.
Pour juice from peaches over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Lightly brown chicken in pan. Remove chicken from pan and add sesame seed to pan. Brown on low.
Remove pan from burner.
Add sugar, cornstarch, ginger and water. Add pineapple, soy sauce and garlic. Cook until thickened.
Add chicken and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: chicken sweet-n-hot
directions: Place chicken strips in large frying pan with 1/4 cup water. Cover.
Simmer.
When water is gone, add lemon juice, hot sauce, garlic and brown sugar (mix in large bowl) and pour over chicken. Add butter.
Mix well.
Simmer over medium heat for 1/2 hour. Keep turning chicken.
Sauce will become thick.

title: dirty rice
directions: Put the water and 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil in a large pot and boil.
In a large skillet add a tablespoon of vegetable oil, brown the ground beef.
Cook the green chilies, minced garlic, bell pepper and onions with ground beef and drain.
Add seasonings. After meat is brown add the rice mixture to the meat and mix well. Then add to the boiling water and follow instructions on the package.
Usually takes about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked, fried and grilled pork chops
directions: Season pork chops to taste.

title: tim's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir while cooking over low heat until sugar dissolves; cool and store covered.

title: easy corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolk slightly, stir in pancake mix and corn.
Fold in beaten egg whites;
drop by large spoonful into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown; drain on paper towels.
Serve with maple syrup, if desired.

title: strawberry-nana shake
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients. Blend until smooth and frothy.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Put flour in a Baggie. Put pickles in flour a few at a time. Shake to coat with flour. Carefully place in hot grease. Fry until brown (like frying squash).

title: toffee
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture reaches 310° or hard crack on a candy thermometer.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Spread on cooled candy.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Let harden and then break into pieces.

title: hearty herbed lentils and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer 1 hour.
Stir occasionally to prevent stirring, as rice will absorb nearly all the liquid.
Can also be put in crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: one hour rolls(my all-time favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dissolve yeast in water and let set. Combine buttermilk (or milk and lemon juice mixture), sugar, oil and salt.
Sift flour and soda in a large bowl.
Mix yeast with buttermilk mixture and add to flour.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: corn-rice-cheese casserole
directions: Cook yellow rice according to package directions.
Mix yellow rice, corn and soup.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and begins to brown.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils.
Put ham bone or ham hocks into boiling water. Cook until tender, about 25 minutes.

title: veg-medley
directions: Mix together.
Place in tightly covered casserole dish.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: rice mushroom casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in oblong baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dinner-in-a-bundle
directions: Place each piece of chicken in a large square of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle generously with spices.
Divide vegetables equally and place on top of chicken portions.
Spoon on soup and sprinkle with spices.
Twist foil on top to seal bundle.
Bake at 400° for 60 minutes.
Can also cook on grill.

title: creamy potato bake(for the grill)
directions: Place sliced potatoes and onion on 22 x 18-inch piece of heavy-duty foil.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cheese, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Fold up foil around potatoes; add chicken broth.
Seal edges tightly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake in a Bundt cake pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brown sugar coffee cake
directions: Mix together with fingertips brown sugar, oleo, flour and salt.
Remove one cup.
Now add remaining ingredients.
After you mix this, put in pan and sprinkle on top the one cup you saved from first mixture.
Bake in a greased pan in a moderate oven.

title: green beans and mushrooms
directions: Saute garlic and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in onion; set aside.
Steam beans until tender-crisp.
Combine beans and mushroom mixture.
Add dill weed and ground pepper.
Garnish with nuts.
Serve immediately.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Oil a 7 x 11-inch pan.
In pan, put 1 cup hot water.
Mix in Jell-O until dissolved and add whole cranberry and lemon juice. Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients. Add on top when completely solid.

title: potato supreme
directions: Mix ingredients well and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Put the cornflake and butter mixture on top.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease 1
large tube or Bundt pan.
Place rolls in pan. Mix butterscotch pudding, with brown sugar and sprinkle on top of rolls.
Mix
white
sugar, cinnamon and pecans and sprinkle on top of
rolls.
Melt
butter and pour on top of rolls.
Let rolls sit overnight
on counter in kitchen.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let
set
for
to
15 minutes and turn out on dish; pull apart.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Add all ingredients; mix with spoon until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Add jello and cream cheese; stir until well blended.
Add nuts.
Cool.	Add whipped cream carefully, folding it in to get marbled effect.
Pour into a mold and let congeal.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cook until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Beat until creamy.
Spread on cake.

title: fajitas
directions: Dice meat into squares or thin strips. Marinate in teriyaki sauce at least 30 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix all together to make stiff dough.
Roll out very thin on floured board.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Slice 1/4-inch wide and let dry 2 hours.
Drop into boiling broth; cook uncovered about 10 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cube cooked chicken.
Dice celery and drain peas.
Mix lemon juice and salt with chicken, celery, peas and grated onion.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add cut up eggs.
When you are ready to serve, add 1 cup or more of mayonnaise, sufficient to hold the mixture together.
Make salad moist.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar; add eggs.	Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Cook for 15 minutes and remove from pan. Mix
cup
of
confectioners sugar and juice of 1 lemon and pour over cake.

title: ozark pudding* * * * *
directions: A neighbor, who was born in Holland, gave me this soup recipe. One day to be different, I added the kielbasa and really liked it.
The Ozark Pudding is Bess Truman's that I first tried in Clovis, New Mexico.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet cook beef and onion.
Stir in flour, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to low and stir in soup; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: caramel nut corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pop
popcorn.
Divide
into
two parts. Put into two 9 x 12-inch pans.
Add 1 cup peanuts into each pan. Into pot on top
of
stove
over
medium heat, melt butter, sugar, Karo, vanilla and salt.
Cook until boils; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour
on
top
of popcorn and peanuts, halving between two pans.
Put
pans
into oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15
minutes.
Pour
out
onto
wax paper, stirring to keep from sticking together.
Cool.
Store.

title: believe it or not cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 375° for not more than 10 minutes.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Beat eggs, shortening and sugar.
Add spices, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add buttermilk.
Gradually add flour.
Fold in berries.

title: chicken with cucumbers and dill
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet and add chicken.
Cook about 8 minutes or until chicken is brown on both sides.
Remove from heat and keep warm.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in same skillet.
Add cukes; stir to coat. Sprinkle remaining salt and pepper over cukes; cook 2 minutes. Stir in dill weed.
Push cucumbers to side of skillet.
Return chicken and any collected juice to skillet.
Cook 2 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Place chicken on serving platter. Arrange cukes around chicken.
Add lemon juice to juice in skillet and pour over chicken.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: fruit slush
directions: Put sugar and water together.
Let cool.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Put in container and freeze.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Add rest of ingredients to them while hot.
Let marinate several hours.
Will keep long time in refrigerator.

title: out of this world
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool before spreading on mixture of cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding with milk and spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Put whipped cream on top of pudding mixture.

title: baked tuna salad
directions: Mix and put into casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Cook broccoli and place on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken chunks onto broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and juice; pour onto chicken.
Add shredded cheese and crumbs; sprinkle melted butter on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed and let cool.
Combine cream cheese, dry pudding and milk with electric mixer.
Spread mixture over cooled cake, spread drained pineapple over mixture, then cover with whipped cream.

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Miracle Whip.
Add just enough Miracle Whip to make spreadable.
Stores about 2 weeks. Good on a sandwich with ham.

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla.
Add melted butter.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8 pan at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs; stir in sugar.
Stir in cornmeal and flour.
Add milk and butter; add vanilla and vinegar. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: miniature frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into paper cupcake liners in 2 1/4-inch muffin tins.
Freeze and store in plastic bag after individual servings are frozen or pour into 8 x 8-inch pan. Freeze.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: mexi-cali casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add chili seasoning mix, whole kernel corn, tomatoes and green pepper.
Have ready the elbow macaroni.
Add to hamburger mixture and heat.
Place in baking dish; top with Cheddar taco seasoned cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Delicious!!!!

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: *One half cup milk may be substituted instead of tomato sauce.

title: stir-fried broccoli and carrots(low-fat)
directions: Spray wok or 12-inch skillet with nonstick cooking spray; heat until hot.
Add ginger root and garlic; stir-fry about 1 minute or until lightly browned.
Add broccoli, carrots and onion; stir-fry 1 minute.
Stir in broth and salt; cover and cook about 3 minutes or until carrots are crisp-tender.
Mix cornstarch and cold water; stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir about 10 seconds or until thickened.
Add water chestnuts, mushrooms and oyster sauce; cook and stir for 30 seconds.
Serves 4.

title: liver loaf
directions: Cover liver with hot water; simmer 5 minutes.
Drain liquid and reserve for stock.
Put liver and onion through food chopper using medium blade.
Add remaining ingredients except bacon to the ground liver mixture.
Form into loaf in a 5 x 9-inch pan.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: giant snickerdoodles
directions: In a large bowl with mixer on medium speed, cream butter, sugar and eggs until smooth and fluffy.
In a separate bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and stir until well blended.
Refrigerate dough for 30 minutes.

title: italian sausage bread
directions: Place frozen bread in greased bread pans.
Let rise until pans are full.
Remove sausage from casing and cook in frying pan until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Take bread dough, one loaf at a time, and roll out to about 1/4-inch thick.
Brush dough with olive oil and then sprinkle with half of the sausage, half of the onion and some Parmesan cheese, garlic salt and some black pepper if you like.
Roll up like you would a jelly roll and cut into about 1/2-inch slices.
Place into greased baking pans with sides of slices touching.
Let rise until about double in size. Cook in a 375° oven until browned.

title: scallops provencale
directions: If using sea scallops, cut into 1 1/2 inch pieces, pat dry. Mix flour, salt and pepper; coat scallops with flour mixture. Heat oil in 10-inch skillet.
Cook scallops in oil 4 to 5 minutes, turning carefully until light brown.
Remove to serving plate. Cook garlic in margarine in 1-quart saucepan over low heat for about 2 minutes; stir frequently until brown.
Pour over scallops. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Makes 3 servings.

title: cauliflower and cheese puffit
directions: Cook cauliflower in water to barely cover; drain.
Place in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Top with cheese.
Slice bread horizontally to make 2 slices.
Spread 1 side of each with mayonnaise (1 teaspoon each) and the other with the mustard.
Place mustard side up.
Beat remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove and place under broiler until brown. Yield:
2 servings.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Put chips and unsweetened chocolate in pan on top of a pan of hot water and melt.
Then after removing from heat, add peanut butter.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan (bottom buttered).
Then stir up melted chips and spread on top. Cut into squares and refrigerate.
When set, cut again.
Keep in cool place.

title: potted beef
directions: Cook the sliced onions in a bit of butter until just limp and tender.
Use them to line a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, over the bottom and up the sides if you can manage it.

Add a layer of beef, a layer of carrots, then repeat, seasoning each layer with salt and pepper and a few drops of soy sauce, until all is used. Make up mashed potatoes or use leftovers; spread over meat with a nice swirl, then trickle the cream over.
Top with crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 400° until heated through, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crock-pot turkey breast
directions: Wash and pat dry turkey breast.
Season lightly with salt. Place in crock-pot with 1 stick of margarine.
Turn on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Great to do overnight.
Very moist.

title: banana bread
directions: Crush bananas.
Cream with sugars and shortening.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 75 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix the first eight
ingredients and pat evenly into 9 x 5-inch glass loaf dish.
Brush meat loaf with a mixture of remaining ingredients or brush with catsup or barbecue sauce alone.

title: holiday salad
directions: *Canned milk can be whipped by adding lemon juice.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, cocoa and soda.
Mix together water, vinegar, oil and vanilla.
Stir the two mixtures together. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 11-inch pan at 350°.

title: tacos (soft)
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add seasoning and water.
Mix and simmer for 5 minutes.
Heat 1/4 inch of oil in skillet.
Fry tortillas for 2 seconds, then turn and fry 2 more seconds.
Drain on paper towel.
Top tortillas with:

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box, then add Cool Whip.
Mix both then place wafers in bowl and slice bananas over wafers.
Pour mixture over; repeat until mixture is all used.
Place in refrigerator and cool.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: grossmommy's taffy
directions: Combine
all
ingredients except gelatin.
Boil to hard ball. Soak
gelatin
in cold water and add.
Remove from heat and cool. Butter
hands and pull until firm.
Using scissors, cut into bite size pieces.

title: christmas wreath punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Mix thoroughly. Add ginger ale and ice ring just before serving.

title: salt dough
directions: Measure the cornstarch and baking soda into a pot.
Mix and add 2 1/2 cups of cold water.
Place on medium heat.
Stir for about 5 minutes until the mixture thickens.
Remove from the heat. Cover the pot with a wet paper towel.
When cool, knead for about 5 minutes, working on a surface covered with wax paper.
Objects must air dry before painting.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a blender, then pour into a mixing bowl.
Add yeast, salt and flour.
Beat and add 6 to 7 cups whole wheat flour.
Knead 6 minutes.
Oil dough and let rise once. Punch down and shape into 4 small loaves.
Let rise in oiled pans until doubled in size in a barely warm oven.
Turn oven to 375° and bake 10 minutes, then decrease temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan and cool on rack. Store in plastic bags when completely cool.

title: chicken fajita pizza
directions: In a large skillet, over medium-high heat, stir-fry chicken in oil for 5 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Stir in chili powder, salt and garlic powder.
Add onions and green pepper; stir-fry an additional 1 minute, or until vegetables are tender and crisp.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Blend sugar and cinnamon in a bowl; set aside. Grease a 10-inch Bundt or tube pan and dust with 1 tablespoon sugar/cinnamon mixture. Blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened. Beat as directed on cake mix package.
Pour half of the batter into pan. Sprinkle with remaining sugar/cinnamon mixture, then top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.
Cool cake in pan, top side up, for 15 minutes before removing.

title: toffee brownie trifle
directions: Prepare and bake brownies according to package directions for cake-like brownies, using a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Cool completely on a wire rack. In a mixing bowl, beat the milk and pudding on low speed for 2 minutes. Fold in whipped topping. Cut the brownies in 1-inch cubes; place half in a 3-quart glass trifle bowl or serving dish. Cover with half of the pudding. Repeat layers. Sprinkle with chopped candy bars. Refrigerate leftovers. Yield: 16 servings.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Bake in a tube pan 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butterscotchers(cookies)
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Remove from heat. Add sugars and Pet milk.
Blend well. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients and lemon rind.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and spread with the following.

title: sugarless banana nut bread
directions: Sprinkle sweetener over mashed bananas and stir until dissolved.
Beat eggs well and beat into bananas.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add nuts and blend thoroughly into banana mixture until just mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Lower heat to 300° and bake another 35 minutes or until done.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together in a pan over hot water; cool.
Beat the eggs with salt and vanilla.
Continue to beat and slowly add the sugar.
Stir the chocolate into eggs and fold in the sifted flour and chopped nuts.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch pan and bake in an oven preheated to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, egg yolks and salt and add buttermilk with soda.
Add flour and vanilla.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Bake 1 hour and 35 minutes at 375°.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift 2 cups flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture and beat.
Dredge blueberries in remaining flour and fold into batter.
Pour into a tube pan that has been greased with butter and sprinkled with sugar.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(Test after 1 hour.)

title: ground pork burritos
directions: Saute pork with onion until browned and cooked through.
Add green onion, garlic, soy sauce and sesame oil.
Cook on medium low for 2 minutes or until onions are tender.
Warm tortillas at 300° for a few minutes.
Spread 1 tablespoon hoisin sauce on each tortilla.
Divide pork mixture in center of each.
Roll up each tortilla so meat mixture is enclosed tightly.
Garnish with sliced peppers and serve with fried rice.

title: baked chicken kiev
directions: Pound chicken into cutlets about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place 1 tablespoon green onion, 1 tablespoon parsley and 1 tablespoon butter on cutlet and roll up the meat, enclosing the mixture by tucking in the sides.
Roll each roll in flour, then eggs and then bread crumbs.
Brush with melted butter and place on foil lined baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches, sugar and flour in pan.
Cook until thick.
Put unbaked crust in a casserole dish or large ovenproof bowl.
Pour peaches in the crust and fold the crust over the top.
Put butter and sugar on top.
Cook until brown.

title: greens with bacon
directions: In a large pot, heat oil and saute the bacon and garlic for 2 to 4 minutes.
Add the greens and lemon juice.
Cook until the greens are limp, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Season with salt to taste.
Preparation time is 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Add cooked noodles, tuna, green pepper and cheese; stir in the onion and salt.
Add pepper to season the full mixture.
Spoon mixture into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in oven for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°, or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4.
Each serving contains 323 calories.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add cubed cream cheese to hot drained spinach.
Add sauteed onion.
Season with salt and pepper. Put in casserole.
Top with stuffing mix (dry).

title: de-luscious
directions: Combine flour, pecans and margarine.
Press into sheet cake pan with fingers.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Cream powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1/2 container Cool Whip and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread over cooled crust.
Prepare pudding mix with milk.
Spread over cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip; sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Boil rice until fluffy and well done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Slowly add to eggs, sugar and other ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.

title: fruit medley
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill about 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in hot salad oil, then remove. Add onions and cook over low heat until golden, but not brown. Drain off excess oil. Add remaining ingredients. Add chicken and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.

Uncover and cook, turning chicken in sauce occasionally, until chicken is tender and sauce is thick (consistency of catsup), about 45 minutes to 1 hour. Skim off excess fat and remove bay leaves before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar, vanilla flavoring and egg well. Drop by spoonfuls or roll into balls and put on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325 degree preheated oven for 14 minutes. Immediately place Hershey's kiss on top of each baked cookie. Let cool for 5 minutes.

title: "low-fat" angel food delight
directions: Put sliced bananas, strawberries and drained pineapple into bowl.
Mix in 1/2 of Cool Whip (set aside).
Cut off top layer of angel food cake, keeping intact.
With a knife, dig a "dredge" in remaining cake and fill with fruit mixture.
Put top back on cake and spread remaining Cool Whip on cake and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Beat in oil and eggs, one at a time.
Stir in carrots and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zesty gameburger steak
directions: Mix tomato puree, beaten egg, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Add meat; mix all together.
Pour a little dressing into frying pan and put in patties.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade eagle brand milk
directions: Put in blender; mix until smooth.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Same as 1 can of Eagle Brand milk.

title: coke salad
directions: Make Jell-O with hot water and Coke.
When slightly thick, add remaining ingredients.
Pour in bowl and refrigerate.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture. Place flour in a large bowl; add dates, candy and nuts. Stir to coat each piece, then add flour mixture and coconut to creamed mixture. Bake in 10-inch tube pan 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, separate the ladyfingers.
Separate the eggs. Take chocolate mixture off stove; allow to cool.
When cool, add the 4 egg yolks, granulated sugar and vanilla.
Beat the 4 egg whites until stiff; fold into the chocolate mixture.
In a 2-quart casserole, add about 1/4 to 1/2 cup of the sauce.
Add a single row of ladyfingers and repeat to the top, ending with sauce. Chill at least 8 hours.
Spoon out into sauce dishes; top with whipped cream.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased 9 x 16-inch baking dish.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Measure cereal into large bowl; set aside. Microwave chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter in 1-quart bowl on High for 1 minute; stir. Microwave 30 seconds longer or until mixture can be stirred smooth. Stir in vanilla. Pour chocolate mixture over cereal in bowl, stirring until evenly coated. Pour into large plastic Ziploc bag; add powdered sugar. Seal bag; shake until well coated. Spread on waxed paper to cool. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: grits souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Generously grease a 2 quart baking dish. Bring the stock to a boil in a saucepan and slowly stir in grits. Add salt, return to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat, cover and let stand. Meanwhile, beat the egg yolks until light yellow. Whisk the egg whites until stiff peaks form. Combine yolks with grits, then fold in whites. Pour in baking dish and bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until puffy and light golden. Serve immediately.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix the 3 ingredients together.
Put 1/2 of dough between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Roll out to fit pie pan.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: microwave taco casserole
directions: Combine cooked rice and cooked hamburger together.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and microwave 10 to 12 minutes.
Top with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese and let stand 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup crushed taco chips over top and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together.
Add mayonnaise to dip consistency.

title: lacy onion rings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend egg and milk.
Add flour mixture.
Beat only until smooth.
Heat oil in electric skillet to 380°.
Dip onion rings in batter.
Deep fry until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Add salt to taste. Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: s'mores clusters
directions: In a large microwave safe bowl, toss chocolate and oil. Microwave, uncovered at 50 per cent power for 1 1/2

to 2 minutes, or until chocolate is melted, stirring once. Stir in marshmallows and graham crackers. Spoon into paper lined muffin cups, about 1/3 cup each. Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix and pour into greased casserole.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Put in saucepan egg (beaten), lemon juice and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Stir over low heat until it becomes a thin custard.
Take off heat and stir in butter.
Let stand while whipping cream. Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating until it's a whipped consistency.
Fold in custard, then marshmallows and fruit.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 12 hours.
Fifteen minutes before serving, cut bananas up and stir well.
Let stand; serve.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar with butter.
Add tomato soup, applesauce or rhubarb.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: zesty macaroni salad
directions: Prepare Creamettes according to package directions. Drain. Set aside. Gently toss all other ingredients with macaroni.
Cover and chill well. Serves 6 to 8.

title: tuna croquettes with parsley sauce
directions: Combine breadcrumbs, tuna, carrots, milk, egg, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Divide mixture into 6 equal portions, shaping each into a cone.
Place on baking sheet covered with cooking spray and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Parsley Sauce.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple together.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Let set overnight.

title: pea dumplings
directions: Put peas, milk and salt on to heat.
Roll out can of biscuits and cut into strips; drop into pot of peas.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Cook until done.

title: sinfully rich cake
directions: Bake cake according to instructions on box. When done, poke holes all over top of cake. Pour condensed milk over cake and refrigerate overnight. Top with caramel ice cream sauce, Cool Whip and crushed candy bars.

title: 10 bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain the beans.
Add the green pepper and onion. Mix together and add dressing.

title: wakki cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl; add vinegar, oil, water and vanilla.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in a large sheet cake pan. Frost with your favorite powdered sugar frosting.
Don't overbake!

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all; pour into 2 greased cake pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: granola
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients and add last three ingredients; put in large pan and bake at 375° until golden brown. Stir 1 or 2 times.

title: mary's ginger cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients to form a stiff dough.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut; roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° until dry and somewhat firm to the touch, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sarah's salad
directions: Place 1/3 of the salad greens in a bowl; dot with 1/3 of mayonnaise.
Top with 1/3 of the onion slices.
Sprinkle with sugar (about 1 teaspoon!).
Dash with salt and pepper.
Add 1/3 of the peas and cheese.
Repeat layers, seasoning each.
Do not toss.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, crumble bacon over top and toss.

title: french epicurean peas
directions: Partially fry bacon and onions; cook until soft and yellow. Add flour and blend. Add peas and cream. Cook until thick, stirring occasionally. Cook mushrooms in butter 5 minutes. Add to peas and season. (If canned mushrooms are used, do not cook them.) Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix cheese, sour cream and milk and add dried beef, garlic, onion and green pepper.
Heat in crock-pot.
Serve warm with assorted fresh vegetables.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 10-inch skillet melt butter; add onion and celery.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until crisply tender, 4 to 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; add broccoli. Cover; continue cooking until broccoli is broken up, 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in one cup of lukewarm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and let stand until foamy.
Beat eggs.
Add to the yeast mixture.
Then add shortening, melted and cooled.
Combine, then add 1 cup hot water, salt and sugar.
Stir in 6 cups flour.
Grease the top and cover with a tea towel.
Chill overnight.
Knead, adding small amount of flour, to make an elastic dough.
Shape into rolls and place on a greased sheet.
Let rise for 2 hours or until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes or until cooked through and golden brown.

title: pineapple pecan pie
directions: Blend lemon juice with condensed milk.
Drain pineapple and blend all ingredients (except crusts).
Put in pie shells and cool.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk according to package directions.
Set side.
Cut cake into 1 to 2-inch cubes.
Set aside.
In a large glass punch bowl, layer the cake, pudding and fruit ending with pudding.
Garnish with fresh fruit.
Chill 30 minutes and serve.

title: chicken-celery casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt in mixer bowl.
On medium speed, beat margarine and Crisco for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well and add dry ingredients, beating until well combined.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats.
Grease 2 (9 x 13 x 2-inch) pans.
Spread dough evenly and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stained glass fruitcake
directions: Mix together
diced
fruit, apricots, cherries and nuts with 1/2 cup
flour.
Cream
butter
and
sugar well.
Beat in eggs, one at a
time.
Stir
in
lemon juice; add dry ingredients, blending well.
Pour into loaf pans lined with wax paper (9 x 5 x 3-inches).	Bake
at
250°	for 1 1/2 hours or until lightly browned.
This
freezes
really well and can be sliced and toasted any time.

title: b.b.q. sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bottle and store in refrigerator. Makes 4-1/2 to 5 cups of sauce.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Devein and shell shrimp.
Pat dry.
Heat oil in large skillet. Add shrimp and cook 3 minutes over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add butter, garlic, sherry and parsley.
Cook 4 minutes longer, stirring constantly. (May add a bottle of clam juice if more broth is desired.)
Serve with rice or crusty Italian bread to soak up broth.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick butter.
Spread and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until ready to use.
Melt 2 sticks butter.
Add confectioners sugar, salt and egg.
Beat 15 to 20 minutes, scraping sides.
Do not underbeat.
Spread over chilled crumbs.
Slice bananas and mix with Fruit Fresh or lemon juice to prevent browning.
Bananas should be coated.
Layer sliced bananas over sugar mixture.
Sprinkle pineapple tidbits over bananas. Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Place a cherry at center of each square piece to be sliced.
Drizzle with chocolate sauce or serve separately.

title: mexican dip
directions: Serve with tortilla chips.

title: gertie's divinity candy
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, water and salt in saucepan.

Cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved (medium to medium-high heat). Continue cooking on medium heat, without stirring, until small amount of mixture forms a firm ball when dropped in cup of cold water.
Pour half of the syrup mixture over the beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
(Use candy speed on mixer.)
Cook remainder of syrup on medium until small amount dropped in cold water forms a hard thread.
Slowly add remaining syrup to first mixture, stirring constantly, until mixture holds shape.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop by spoonful onto wax paper or spread on a large buttered plate or pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Let cool to set up.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: enchilada surprise
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Place in large casserole dish. Top with 2 cans mild enchilada sauce.
Top with layer of tortilla chips. Top chips with the soup.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: Cook hen in 2-quarts of water or enough to cover. Bring to a boil and cook covered on lower heat until tender, approximately 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Remove from water and let cool. Take chicken off bones and cut up in small pieces.

title: corn casserole
directions: Put corn in casserole; spread with crackers and cheese; dot with butter.
Pour milk, egg and salt over corn mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms(hors d' oeuvre)
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Mix together the crab, cream cheese and croutons until blended.
Mound mixture into mushroom caps.
Sprinkle tops generously with Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Broil until piping hot and delicately browned.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
At the same time, cook noodles according to package direction.
When hamburger is done, drain off grease.
Add soup and add drained, cooked noodles. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Stir in thoroughly and serve.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix well and let stand about 1/2 hour before serving to set flavor.
Can be served plain or on lettuce leaf.

title: blueberry pudding(diabetic)
directions: Combine crushed flakes, cinnamon, sugar substitute, salt, vanilla and melted margarine.
Place blueberries at bottom of baking dish and cover with corn flake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with diabetic whipped topping.

title: quick fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on lightly greased pizza pan.
Bake using package directions.
Cream sugar, cream cheese and vanilla in bowl until light and fluffy.
Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit on filling just before serving.
May add any other favorite fruit such as strawberries, kiwi fruit or bananas.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter pan.
Spread the crushed pineapple, then cherry pie filling, then yellow cake mix, then oleo; top with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: barbecue pig feet
directions: Use pigs feet (as needed).
Cook all together slowly, until sauce starts to thicken enough to take and brush over pigs feet on grill or in oven at 350°.
Cook until they become crisp and brown. Keep putting sauce on pigs feet.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
The longer chilled, the better. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: beat 'n' eat frosting
directions: Place egg white, sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla in a deep bowl.
Mix well.
Add boiling water.
Beat, until stiff peaks form, with an electric mixer.
Will frost 8-inch layer cake. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: baked surprise dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a small buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serve with assorted raw vegetables, crackers and chips.

title: mini cheese tarts
directions: Unfold pie crust and roll into it is thin. Cut rounds from it to fit mini tart pan shells. Press into mini pan. Fill each crust with 1 teaspoon of goat cheese, Feta cheese or Bleu cheese and basil, rosemary or dill. Beat egg with half and half and salt. Spoon this mixture over the cheese in the tart shells. Bake at 375° until puffed, about 25 minutes. These are really simple and good. Makes about 2 dozen tarts.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake and cool crust.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Put peanut oil in your outdoor cooker and heat to 350°.
Wash and clean out turkey.
Season with salt and pepper.
Submerge turkey in oil; cook for 3 minutes per pound.
Remove turkey, drain, let cool for 30 minutes, carve and enjoy.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy; add and blend in sugar and salt. Mold in 1-inch balls and roll in tinted coconut.
Chill or freeze. To tint coconut, sprinkle 2 tablespoons Jell-O (any flavor) over dry coconut in a jar or plastic bag.
Shake until color is even.

title: heavenly chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and shortening until smooth.
Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Gradually add flour, salt and soda.
When well blended, fold in chocolate chips.
Drop onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon balls
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla; cream until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and cinnamon; add to the creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in cornflakes and pecans.
Shape dough into small balls and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lamb with green beans
directions: Brown lamb in butter, then add green beans, onion, celery, green pepper.
Cover and steam until tender, about 45 minutes.
Add tomato puree, water, salt, pepper and cook 15 minutes longer or until done.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: raspberry-filled jelly doughnuts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place melted margarine in small bowl.
In another small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Stir jelly until smooth.
Seal tip of large baster with foil.
Remove rubber bulb.
Spoon jelly into baster; replace bulb.
Prepare and bake biscuits according to package directions.
Immediately dip each hot biscuit in melted margarine, coating all sides.
Roll in sugar mixture, heavily coating all sides of each biscuit.
Remove foil from tip of baster.
Insert baster in side of each biscuit, squeeze.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender (20 to 30 minutes), then cube. Prepare rice as directed.
Mix soup and mix until smooth on low heat.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Brown rice and spaghetti in oil until golden in 2-quart saucepan. Add chicken broth and bring to a boil. Add broccoli and thyme. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally. Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: overnight salad
directions: Mix last three ingredients together.
Combine salad ingredients and toss together.
Pour mix on top of salad.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir when ready to serve.

title: cheese and pasta
directions: Brown beef in oil; drain fat.
Add onion, garlic, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni, drain and rinse.
Pour 1/2 the shells into a deep casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 sauce.
Spread 1/2 sour cream; top with Provolone cheese.
Repeat, ending with Mozzarella cheese. Cover and bake until cheese is brown.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs.
